title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture with sour cream.
Add nuts and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Quick Caramel Frosting.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn and set aside.
In large stew pan boil sugar, syrup (of choice), water and butter until a rolling boil is formed.
Add vanilla and reduce heat to a simmer.
Add popped corn and stir with metal spoons (plastic may melt).
After all corn is coated with syrup mixture, remove from heat.
Using rubber gloves, form corn into balls and place on a greased cookie sheet to cool.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate approximately 20 minutes and serve.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Combine eggs, milk and melted butter.
Add to flour mixture; stir until smooth (batter will be very thin).
Bake on hot griddle, using 1/2 cup to each large pancake (8 or 9-inch).
Keep warm until all are finished.
Serve with sour cream or preserves.
Makes about 8 large pancakes.

title: garlic grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook grits in salted water. Cut cheese into small pieces and stir into hot grits and margarine. Cool. Beat eggs with milk. Fold in slowly. Add garlic salt to taste. Pour in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Bake 1 hour.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, crushed strawberries and juice, strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into crusts.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Garnish with strawberry halves.

title: guacamole
directions: In a blender or food processor combine avocados, cilantro, onion, peppers, garlic, lime juice and salt.
Cover and blend until nearly smooth, stopping and scraping as necessary.
Transfer mixture to a bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap directly touching the surface to prevent darkening.
Chill for up to 24 hours if needed. Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Contains 26 calories per tablespoon.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Line pan with waxed paper.
Grease wax paper.
Beat until fluffy the eggs and sugar.
Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in buttermilk baking mix, nutmeg, pumpkin pie spice and cinnamon.
Pour into pan and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes. Invert onto towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Peel off waxed paper.
Roll up cake and towel from short side.
Place on wire rack and cool completely.
Unroll cake.
Spread with filling. Re-roll cake and refrigerate.

title: garden fresh vegetables
directions: In a wok or large skillet add chopped tomatoes, onion, peppers, garlic and zucchini to your melted butter or oil.
Cook medium-high heat stirring so heat is transferred evenly.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: american pie
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add vegetables and seasonings; stir.
Add tomato soup.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: polynesian dip
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients.
Stir in next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with gingersnaps or shortbread.

title: party mix
directions: Mix together chex cereals, pretzels, oyster crackers, corn nuts, peanuts & mixed nuts in a large bowl. Set aside.
Melt margarine in small bowl. Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, lawrys salt, onion powder & garlic powder, mix well.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mix and toss gently to coat cereal well.
Spread on 2 large cookie sheets.
Pour cheese crackers on top.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring gently every 15 minutes. Cool completely before putting in air tight container.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix butter and flour into sour cream.
Add seasoning.
Put 1 can beans in dish.
Put 1/2 cheese on top, then other can and rest of cheese.
Add cream mixture and then crumbled corn flakes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine with tomatoes, olives, salt and pepper.
Pour salad dressing over and mix well.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; cut into cubes.
Cube Velveeta cheese; chop onion and bacon.
Mix potatoes, cheese, onion and bacon with mayonnaise and season to taste.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be prepared ahead and baked when ready to serve.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Beat sugar, melted butter, egg and milk in a large bowl for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot with bits of butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes until center of cake is done.
Let cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: creamy white chili
directions: In a large sauce pan saute chicken, onion and garlic powder in oil until chicken is no longer pink.
Add beans, broth, chilies and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in sour cream and milk.
Serve immediately.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in sugar and shortening. With spoon, mix in sifted flour until dough is easy to handle. Keep dough soft, almost sticky.

title: prime rib roast at its best
directions: Mix the Accent, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, salt and seasoned pepper together.
Rub into all sides of roast.

title: crock-pot beef and peppers
directions: Cut the steak into serving size pieces.
If desired you can brown the meat in a little hot oil before adding to crock-pot. Place the thinly sliced pepper rings in bottom of crock-pot, reserving a few to place on top of meat if desired.
Arrange meat on peppers, careful not to stack one piece directly on top of another.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat and peppers. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high for about 4 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes and simply seasoned vegetables. Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 34 g, fat 14 g, calories 237.

title: beef and brown rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add mushrooms, onion and green pepper. Saute with beef until onion is tender.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in rice, beef mixture and seasonings.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 375°. Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes until browned and liquid is absorbed.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 1 quart baking dish with non-stick cooking spray.
In a small bowl, combine buttermilk, baking mix, 1 Tbsp. sugar and the cardamon.
Stir until smooth and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine apples, the remaining 1 Tbsp. of sugar and the lemon juice; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring constantly 5 minutes until fruit is soft. Pour into prepared baking dish.
With spoon, evenly drop batter over fruit.
Bake 20-25 minutes, until browned.
Let cool.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Blend until smooth (30 seconds).
Pour into 8 dessert dishes. Chill at least 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in cold water.
In the morning, drain and add 2 quarts fresh water.
Cook until almost tender. Drain.
Add the other ingredients.
Place strips of bacon over beans.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.
Leave, uncovered, the last 20 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave until almost tender.
(Also can be cooked on stove top.)
Blend cheese, soup and milk.
Saute onion in olive oil and add to cheese mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: make your own mulch
directions: Thank you, Lord, for your love for each of us, for your provision for our physical and spiritual needs, for this good food.
May we constantly remember that all these good things which we enjoy are gifts from your hand.
Give us truly grateful hearts, we pray.
Amen

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to a soft ball stage.
Beat, beat, and beat until creamy.
Add pecans.
Drop onto waxed paper.
If it gets hard, add about a teaspoon of half and half each time needed.

title: death by chocolate brownies
directions: Add all ingredients except frosting to prepared brownie mix. Bake according to brownie mix when cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting (try white chocolate frosting).
Slice and serve when cool!

title: dump cake
directions: Empty pineapple into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, covering bottom of pan.
Spoon pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Slice margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Melt and heat thoroughly in crockpot or in saucepan over low heat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fish casserole
directions: If desired, rub a shallow 2-quart baking dish with garlic. Spread dish with margarine, then spinach.
Add the fish fillets and season lightly with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Add onion rings and spread soup on top.
Arrange tomato slices on soup and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake in a 350° oven about 35 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers and mix with vinegar and sugar. Boil 10 minutes. Set off stove for 5 minutes. Add Certo and stir well. Have jars ready to pack immediately.

title: english bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids to 125°.
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in enough more flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 bread pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops also. Cover.
Let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
Especially good toasted and served with butter and honey.

title: rolls (never fail)
directions: Heat milk and margarine together in saucepan until margarine melts.
Pour into large bowl (mixing) to cool 5 to 10 minutes until lukewarm.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and egg.
Mix.
Add 2 cups flour to milk mixture and stir well.
Dissolve yeast and remaining 1 tablespoon sugar in water and add to flour mixture. Stir in enough of remaining flour to make sticky dough.

title: poor man's punch
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Use 1/4 cup mixture, pineapple juice, sugar, ginger ale and water.

title: broccoli-nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Combine broccoli with the soup, mayonnaise and nuts.
Add the eggs and onion and blend well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Melt the butter or margarine and toss with the bread crumbs.
Scatter over top of cheese.
Place in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown the meat on both sides in a large pan.
Lower the heat and add the chopped onion and celery.
Cover and cook over a low heat until the meat leaves the bones.
Remove fat and gristle and shred the meat.
You may prefer to remove the fat prior to cooking so the broth can be used in the sauce.

title: sausage noodle casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish, 8 x 10-inches.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Fold in pie crust. Refrigerator for 4 hours.

title: tamale pie
directions: To make filling, brown ground beef, onions and green pepper; drain. Add the remaining ingredients except for cheese. Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until thickened. Add the cheese, stir until melted. Set aside.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Place pretzels in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put margarine on top. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Cool slightly.
Pour off excess margarine.
Spread cream cheese mixture over lukewarm pretzels. Spread Cool Whip on top and chill.

title: almond roca bars
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg, flour and salt.
Spread in a 15 x 11-inch pan.
Bake	25
minutes at 325°.
Melt chocolate and spread on top of cookies.
Press almonds on top of cookies.

title: spartan "free fer all"
directions: Combine various amounts in a large crock with block of ice. Keep grape juice to a 3 to 1 ratio.
Garnish with bunches of grapes, orange, lemon and lime slices.
Empty all those partially filled bottles you have.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Cut shrimp and oysters into 1/4-inch pieces.
Remove any remaining shell or cartilage from crab meat.
Cook green pepper, onion and celery in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add shrimp, oysters and crab meat.
Cook over low heat until shrimp turn pink and oysters curl at the edges.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to a near boil.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Melt white chocolate in a double boiler.
Add nuts and pretzels; stir well.
Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet in thin layer.
Place in freezer until cold, 10 minutes.
Remove and turn (upside-down).
Break into pieces as peanut brittle.

title: quick cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Add cooked pudding to dry cake mix and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Put chocolate chips sprinkled over batter. Add nuts over batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake or cake will be dry and tough.
No icing needed.

title: refrigerator fruit salad
directions: Fold cottage cheese into Cool Whip.
Sprinkle gelatin over mixture and blend well.
Fold in fruit cocktail, marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake
potatoes
until
tender.
Scoop
out the insides, making potato
shells.
Mash the potatoes with the butter and enough milk
to
do
the job, keeping the mixture very stiff. Add
the sour
cream,
ham
and green onions, then scoop this mixture back into the potato shells.
Top with cheese and bake until nicely browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Combine with other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter melt oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat
margarine until very creamy.
Add powdered sugar. Mix well.
Add	vanilla
flavoring,
flour
and salt.
Stir in oatmeal with
spoon.
Roll out in balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake
at
350° for 18 to 22 minutes until light brown. Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: With an electric mixer, cream 1 stick of butter, oil and the sugar.
Beat in the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in the buttermilk and 1 teaspoon of the vanilla. Stir in 1/4 cup of the cocoa powder, flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and salt until the mixture is just combined.
Fold in the grated zucchini, which has been patted dry with paper towels. Stir in the chocolate chips and the walnuts.
Pour the batter into 2 well-greased 9-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Let the cakes cool 10 minutes, then turn out of pans.
Cool completely on racks.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in small ovenproof dish. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with Town House crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream, butter, cheese and hash browns in a large dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Save some onions to sprinkle on top after baking.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Put chicken and onion in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with tarragon and salt to taste.
Bake in covered pan for 45 minutes at 375°. Uncover and bake until golden brown (1/2 hour).
Serve with wedge baked potatoes.

title: icebox (refrigerator) cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg; add vanilla.
Measure and sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Sift dry ingredients into butter mixture.
Add chopped nut meats. Form into long roll (roll in wax paper) and chill for at least 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Dough keeps well 4 to 6 days.

title: rice milk
directions: Blend until smooth; chill and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix oil and flour; add enough milk to make thin white cream sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place peas, carrots, onion and celery in casserole dish.
Add layers of chicken.
Pour in cream sauce and broth.
Top with biscuits and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onions and green pepper in small amount of fat.
Add ground beef.
Brown and then pour off excess fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer for at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Use 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Put 2 or 3 tablespoons, according to taste, in cup of boiling water.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Add sugar, salt and butter to hot milk.
Add potatoes and some coconut in mixture.
Put marshmallows and coconut on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: water chestnuts and zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken tempters
directions: In a medium sized fry pan, melt butter.
Add onion, green pepper and saute 2-3 minutes.
Stir in chicken, cheese, sour cream, worcestershire sauce, salt and cayenne.
Blend well and set aside.
Prepare pie crust mix according to package directions. Roll very thin and cut into 2 inch circles.
Place about 1 tsp of filling in the center of half of them.
Top with the other half and press sides together with fork to seal.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg whites.
Bake at 450 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: old-fashioned fried apple pies
directions: In large Dutch oven, place frozen apples over low heat. Stir in
1 cup sugar and simmer until done.
Sprinkle cinnamon (use more, if desired) across cooked apples.
Allow to cool to room temperature
so it won't melt the dough while frying.
In large mixing
bowl,
pour
in sifted flour.
Cut in shortening and blend in
milk
to
form dough.
Pinch off golf ball size dough.
Roll on
floured
surface and spoon in cooled apples. Fold and seal. In large electric skillet with hot oil, put in pies.
Brown evenly on both sides.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix real good.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Add hot Tabasco sauce to taste.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix baking soda with sour cream; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add sour cream mixture.
Roll on floured surface; cut out cookies.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with additional sugar (can be colored sugar or sprinkles) and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp and season with Season-All and garlic.
Place in casserole dish and cover with pats of butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn shrimp over and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pepperoni balls
directions: Prepare roll mix according to package directions, omitting egg and using 1 cup water.
Place 1 cheese cube with 1 pepperoni slice.
Wrap each with a small piece of dough shaping into a ball. Fry in deep oil for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour Italian dressing over warm potatoes; chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onion and chopped egg whites.
Sieve yolks and mix with mayonnaise, mustard and sour cream.
Fold into salad. Add salt and celery seed to taste.
Chill 2 hours.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix the flour, butter and milk together.
Combine the vegetables, soup and chicken. Pour 1/3 of batter in baking dish. Add vegetable mix and pour remainder of batter on top. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: cocoa puffs
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, then Cocoa Puffs (can use more if mix is too soupy. Drop on waxed paper; allow to harden. Store single file with wax paper between rows.

title: mom's peach pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to boil. Remove from heat and cool. (I put pan and all in freezer for 20 to 25 minutes.) Add 2 cups fresh peaches (if available), partially drained, to cooled mixture. Pour into cooled crust and top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: teriyaki tidbits(excellent with beef, chicken, pork, shrimp)
directions: Heat approximately 1 cup soy sauce, 1/2 teaspoon ginger and 1/2 cup brown sugar until the sugar dissolves.
Let cool. Marinate your favorite meat overnight.
Remove from marination and broil as you normally would.
When the meat cools, cut into bite size pieces and skewer with a toothpick and pineapple chunk.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Remove ingredients from sides of pan before cooking.
When mixture begins to get hot, add margarine, stirring constantly.
After mixture has boiled up in the pan and gone back down, begin testing
for doneness by dropping a few drops of fudge mixture in cool water. When you can make a ball from the mixture, then remove pan from heat.
Have 3 buttered platters ready to
pour the mixture in. Add a teaspoon of vanilla to each platter.
Let set for about 5 minutes.
Beat each platter with upward strokes to allow cooling. Beat until mixture loses shine and will hold shape when dropped by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Recipe yields 60 pieces.

title: creamy potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Coat an 8-inch square baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion together.
Add rest of ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° or cook on medium in crock-pot.

title: hominy saute
directions: Drain the hominy. Saute in a small amount of oil or margarine, the hominy, onion and green or red pepper.
Season with black pepper.

title: 24-hour vegetable salad
directions: Place lettuce or spinach in the bottom of a bowl about 8 inches in diameter.
If desired, sprinkle with salt and pepper. Layer mushrooms, broccoli or peas atop.
Then layer carrots. Arrange egg slices and bacon over vegetables.
Top with 1/2 cup of the cheese and green onions.

title: spinach raspberry salad
directions: Wash tomatoes and spinach.
Drain oranges.
Place spinach in a large bowl; add dressing and toss to coat.
Divide into 4 servings.
Top with oranges, tomatoes and sunflower seeds.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups crushed pretzels with sugar and butter.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Pat onto cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and 1/2 cold water. Add strawberries.
Refrigerate.
When this mixture begins to gel, spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until set.

title: dressed up mullet
directions: Note:
Redfish or drum may be used.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, vanilla, and milk.
Sift and mix flour and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Chill several hours.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 300° for 10-15 minutes.
Take from oven and remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature; cut beef into small pieces.
Mix everything together.
Mold into a loaf. Decorate with slices of ripe olives and parsley around base. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate fudge candy
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler; add can of sweetened milk and stir until well blended.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan lined with wax paper.
When thoroughly chilled, cut in squares.

title: holiday mince squares
directions: Combine in large bowl oats, flour, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add butter and cut in until mixture is in fine crumbs. Pat 2/3 of crumb mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon evenly over top mincemeat.
Mix nuts into remaining crumb mixture; sprinkle over mincemeat.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, cool in pan and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: oyster cracker munchies
directions: Warm oil.
Add seasonings to oil.
Pour over crackers and toss until oil has been absorbed.

title: aim cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, brown sugar and margarine until smooth.
Add the egg, salt and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in baking soda, flour and chocolate chips.
Chill for best results.
Make dough into balls one inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until pale brown.
Yields 24 AIM cookies.

title: ham ball
directions: Melt cream cheese at room temperature; cut up ham.
Mix dressing and cream cheese together.
Add all ingredients and shape into a ball.
For best results, let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and whipped topping.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Pour into mold and freeze until set.
Serves 12.

title: jambalaya
directions: Add sausage, chicken, onion, green pepper and celery into a 3-quart saucepan.
Saute until onions are transparent and chicken is no longer pink, about 8 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Drain clam juice into a 2-cup measuring cup.
Add clams to chicken mixture. Drain stewed tomatoes into same measuring cup as clam juice.
Add drained tomatoes to pan.
Add water to measuring cup with clam and tomato juices to equal 2 cups.
Add rice to pan and add 2 cups liquid measured to pan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in shrimp; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the ingredients until smooth.
Roll out to 3/16-inch thick and spread with date filling.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Refrigerate overnight; slice and bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until ingredients are moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into three (9-inch) cake pans, floured and greased.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, oleo and vanilla together.
Add pecans.
Ice cake.
Keep cake stored in ice box.
Will keep for several days.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and dry pudding mix together in a large bowl. Add marshmallows and Cool Whip; mix well and chill before serving.

title: sweet potato pie(a southern favorite!)
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mixer.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: peanut butter fruit salad
directions: May add other fruit.

title: aunt hazel's icing(for decorating cakes)
directions: Beat with electric beater until you feel it and it doesn't stick to your fingers.
Can either spread on cake with spreading knife or put into decorating bags to make designs on cakes.

title: hearty beef and potatoes
directions: Brown beef and drain.
In a slow cooker arrange layers of potatoes and ground beef.
Mix other ingredients except for cream and pour over meat and potatoes.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours. Turn to high and pour cream over all.
Cover and cook on high for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Lightly beat 2 eggs in a large bowl.
Add ground beef, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley, 1 1/2 teaspoons basil, minced garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix well to combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread 1/2 mixture in the bottom of a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir together 1 egg, Ricotta cheese, 1/2 teaspoon basil, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix well.
Spread over meat.
Top with remaining meat mix.
Spread to cover cheese.
Pour tomato sauce over the top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: glazed chicken bits
directions: Using wire whisk, in small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken and rice.
In 8-inch microwavable glass pie plate, arrange chicken cubes.
Pour honey mixture over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Vent plastic wrap and microwave chicken mixture on High (100%) for 2 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Let stand for 1 minute, until chicken is cooked through.
Serve over rice.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Bake in greased pan about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix; pat into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine one husband, one wife and a number of children, assorted sizes (these are optional but add a delightful flavor). Using a strong unity, blend well together.
Add a pinch of helpfulness, a sprig of loyalty and a dash of patience.
Mix generous portions of smiles and a few drops of tears.
Fold into mixture and stir until light consistency forms.
Sprinkle with kindness and garnish with love.
This delicacy, called family happiness, should not be taken with a grain of salt, but if completely digested is good for heart nutrition.
Regular servings provide minimum requirements for healthy, congenial living.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until finely blended.
Beat egg; add to milk.
Stir into dry ingredients and beat vigorously.
Pour the mixture into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: creamed squirrel
directions: Roll squirrel in flour mixture.
Heat oil and brown squirrel in frying pan.
Remove squirrel.
Add onions and mushrooms and fry 5 minutes.
Add squirrel, wine, thyme and parsley.
Mix well. Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove squirrel from pan and cool.
Add enough water to pan to give 1 cup liquid.
Add cream to this.
Bring to a boil and thicken with flour.
Add meat to sauce.
Simmer, then serve.

title: very best tea
directions: Boil water and sugar 10 minutes.
Add loose tea.
Steam 10 minutes.
Strain into 2-quart pitcher and fill with water.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and nuts in a large bowl and set aside.
Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine into a hard boil.
Add vanilla and pour over oatmeal mixture.
Mix and drop on wax paper or foil. Let set until hard.

title: mary ann's vegetarian delight
directions: Rinse lentils and discard pebbles.
Transfer to a large pot and add carrots, onion stuck with cloves, broth or stock, bay leaf and thyme.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer; skim any foam that may appear. Cover and cook for about 25 minutes or until lentils are tender, but still hold their shape; do not overcook.

title: corn flake caramels
directions: Place margarine, milk and caramels in large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add cornflakes; mix well until coated.
With back of spoon, press mixture evenly and gently into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into bars when firm.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2 1/2-quart baking dish in 350° oven.
Combine dry ingredients and milk in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Top with peaches.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar and salt. Then add the nutmeg, vanilla and milk.

Pour into a 9 inch pie crust. Bake just until a knife inserted into filling comes out clean. The center may still look a bit soft, but will set later. Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes, then at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and salt in saucepan. Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream, chips and vanilla. Stir until melted and mixture is smooth. Stir in nuts. Pour in buttered 10 1/2 X 15 inch pan. Cool. Cut.

title: mom's meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate ribs, chicken or steaks at least 15 to 20 minutes before grilling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Make vanilla pudding or pie
filling.
Crumble 1/2 of baked cake in bottom of punch bowl, then add 1/2 of vanilla pudding or pie filling.
Slice 1/2 of the bananas and place on top of pudding.
Next, add 1/2 of crushed pineapple on top of bananas.
Then put 1/2 of strawberry or cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and repeat process.
Place cherries and nuts on top for Christmas.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: In wok or skillet, stir-fry beef, garlic and salt in hot oil. Stir in soy sauce.
Cook, covered, 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove meat and set aside.
Add broccoli and 3/4 cup water to wok.
Bring to boiling.
Stir, then continue cooking, covered, 2 to 5 minutes more.
Add meat.
Combine cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into center of meat mixture.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes more or until thickened and bubbly.
Serve with hot rice.

title: beef stew for the crock-pot(crock-pot on low all day.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot. Do not brown meat.
A magic brown gravy develops during cooking.
Stir occasionally if you are at home.
I cook mine in a crock-pot on low all day. Serves 6.
This recipe is delicious with biscuits and a green salad.

title: layered salad
directions: Beginning with lettuce, layer ingredients in a suitable glass pan or bowl in order given above.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant lengthwise, about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry in oil, changing if necessary. Drain well on paper towel.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, scoop sauce on bottom.
Then place eggplant meat and both cheeses.
Repeat in layers until ingredients are done.
Cover with sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand before cutting and serving.

title: cornmeal mix
directions: Combine in large bowl; cut in shortening until well blended. Put in covered container and store in cool place.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the pumpkin, eggs, sugar, spices and sweet condensed milk.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Crumble the dry cake mix over the top of the pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Drizzle the melted butter on top of everything.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix soup and melted cheese together; add hominy and Ro-Tel. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom wine sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 7 minutes or until slightly thickened. Great with chicken.
Use beef broth and red wine or burgundy wine for beef.

title: macaroon cake
directions: Separate eggs, letting whites warm to room temperature. Grease a 10-inch tube pan. Beat egg yolks with shortening & butter at high speed until well blended. Gradually add sugar until light & fluffy (amount of sugar can be reduced). Add almond extract, then flour (in 1/4's) and milk (in 1/3's) beating at low speed. Blend in coconut well. Beat egg whites until stiff peak forms and gently fold into batter with wire whisk or rubber scraper. Bake 2 hours at 300° or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes on wire rack.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese slices).
Spread on bread (all the way to edges) and put under broiler for about 15 minutes until done or brown.
Put Mozzarella slices on top and broil until cheese is melted.
(May also slice 3 medium tomatoes on top with Mozzarella.)

title: chocolate-zucchini bread
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine zucchini, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with zucchini mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: relatively healthy blueberry cheesecake
directions: Bowl 1:
Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk, oil, egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Pour batter into 9 x 9-inch pan and pour blueberries over batter.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in a crock-pot or chafing dish.
Heat and put sausages in.
Let heat thoroughly.
Use toothpicks.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients in a bowl.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredient to first mixture.
Add nut meats. Stir well.
Put in a Pam-sprayed 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Cream
butter
with
sugar;
add one egg at a time, but thoroughly
after
each addition.
Stir in preserves and milk, then
baking
powder,
cinnamon and flour that has been sifted together.
Bake in oven at 325° until done.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine baking soda and sour cream; mix and let set while mixing other ingredients.
Cream butter, margarine and sugar with electric mixer until well blended to creamy texture.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Add flavoring and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: m&m fudge bars
directions: Mix together.
Reserve 3/4 cup; pat rest of mixture in an 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put 1 small box of rice in baking dish.
Mix until blended, 1 can mushroom soup, 1 can celery soup and 1 cup milk.
Pour over rice.
Stir together.
Place chicken breasts on top of mixture. Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°, until chicken is tender.

title: cracker candy
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line saltines on buttered, foil-lined 15 x 10-inch baking sheet with sides.
In saucepan, bring sugar and butter to a boil; let boil fully 1 minute.
Pour over crackers, spreading to cover saltines.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes until bubbly all over.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 3 minutes until chocolate is melted.
Spread over saltines. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool completely; break apart in small pieces.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute butter, parsley, and onions.
Add flour, Italian dressing, and potato chips.
Combine the mixture with cold milk and heat to desired temperature.
Serve.

title: salmon log
directions: Combine salmon, cream cheese, nuts and horseradish and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and flour; mix well.
Add milk and corn.
Cook in a 2-quart casserole at 325°.
Cook until set in center.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Combine the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve dry yeast and sugar in water. Scald milk; add Crisco, sugar, salt, and flour. Stir in flour mixture (about 4 cups at a time); beat. Add eggs and beat. Add yeast mixture; knead well. Place in greased pan and cover. Let rise; knead again. Divide dough into 4 parts. Roll out 1/2 inch thick. Cut doughnuts and place on greased paper until they double in size. Fry in deep fat.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour, then combine with eggs, milk, butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: spinach and brown rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in a large skillet; add onions, mushrooms and garlic and saute until just tender.
Do not overcook.
In a bowl, combine egg, flour, cottage cheese and spinach; mix well and add rice, pepper, thyme and 1 tablespoon of Parmesan cheese.
Stir in sauteed vegetables and spoon in a lightly greased 12 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese and sunflower seeds.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 8.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour 15 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Sift together and set aside the first 3 ingredients.
Combine and heat to boiling in 2-quart pot, stirring, the next 3 ingredients, then add to pot, flour mixture and beat with mixer until well blended.
Add last 3 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 22 minutes.
Frost cake while still warm.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Grease 9x13 pan.
Dump applesauce and pineapple into pan. Spread 1 package yellow cake mix over that.
Pour melted butter or margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over all.
Do not stir.

title: fiesta dip(from tyk)
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in a heat-proof dish.
Heat in oven at 350° until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Also good with Doritos.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain thoroughly.
Add taco mix and heat through. Cover bottom and sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Pour beef mixture over tortillas.
Place a layer of tortillas over meat mixture and set aside.
Combine Ricotta or cottage cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and egg.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with lettuce, tomatoes, olives and Cheddar cheese.
Cut into lasagna size squares and serve.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor.
Place in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until brown.
Great for cream pies.

title: grandma krueger's ice box cookies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar, butter and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll in wax paper 1 inch around.
Chill; slice and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 100-120 cookies.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets in 2-cup measuring cup and add vinegar and sugar and enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat.
Add jello and horseradish.
Place in mold in refrigerator.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Combine melted chocolate, sugar, syrup, salt and milk. Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Cook to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat; add butter and cool until just warm. Add vanilla and beat until spreading consistency. Frost lightly between layers and top and sides of cake.

title: vegetable cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine with milk and Cheddar cheese. Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill well and serve with crackers.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper to taste.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Brush butter on chicken and bake 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and carefully turn chicken over.
Set aside.

title: easy  biscuits
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Using a pastry blender, blend in the 2 tablespoons Crisco until the mixture is coarse and grainy.
Then, using a fork, stir in the buttermilk.
Do not overmix.
Put on a floured board and knead just a few times.
Pat out the dough to about 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with a floured biscuit cutter or a glass.
Do not handle the dough too much or it will get tough.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 3 layers or large sheet pan at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: gourmet meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, bread crumbs and chopped meat thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper, 1/2 teaspoon each.
Saute onion and garlic until translucent.
Mix this and tomato sauce thoroughly with mixture of meat.
Lastly, add can of ice water and blend.
Place in loaf pan. Add 4 slices of thick bacon over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Voila!

title: baked brown rice
directions: Place rice, consomme and margarine in casserole dish.
Bake in covered dish for 45 minutes at 350° or until done to taste.

title: leb kuchen(good cookies)
directions: In saucepan, bring honey, molasses or sorghum and dark brown sugar to boil.
Let cool, then add 1 pound flour.
Combine eggs, light brown sugar, pecans and citron.
Sift together mace, cinnamon, soda and 2 pounds flour.
Mix all together, bringing to bread dough consistency.
Add extra flour as needed.
Put in covered container and let sit at room temperature for 3 days. (Don't peek!)

title: salsa al basilico(quick 20 minute basil sauce)
directions: Saute chopped garlic until golden.
Add tomatoes and basil. Cook 20 minutes over low to medium heat, stirring often.
Pour over cooked pasta.
Garnish with additional fresh basil if desired.

title: creamy strawberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter a 10 x 2 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Mix together cracker crumbs, ginger and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir in melted butter. Transfer to spring-form pan, press down. Refrigerate crust 30 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, lemon zest, vanilla and remaining 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat at low speed until creamy and smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until thoroughly blended.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour batter into crust in pan and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in middle of oven 1 1/4 hours.
Turn oven off and prop door open a few inches. Let cake rest in oven for 1 hour.
Transfer to rack and let cool to room temperature.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cut with electric knife.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: In a large saucepot, heat oil.
Add flour and cook over low heat, stirring often until roux turns dark brown in color and develops a nutty aroma.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Slowly add chicken broth a little at a time, stirring after each addition.
Bring to a boil.

title: beef and cabbage casserole(diet)
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add onions, tomato sauce, juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Put layer of cabbage in 2-quart casserole.
Then cover with meat mixture.
Repeat, cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put flounder in 9-inch baking pan. Place garlic, pepper and parsley on top.
Bake at 400°.

title: banana split pie
directions: Make crust with cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo.
Put in pan. Mix oleo, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla together and beat 10 minutes.
Slice bananas over filling.
Cover with pineapple (drained) and Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries, nuts and coconut.

title: chicken dressing
directions: *You may substitute the 2 1/2 cups chicken broth with 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can chicken broth.

title: peach cream
directions: For each drink, put all of the ingredients in blender and blend 30 seconds.
Serve.
Tastes like a creamsicle!

title: sweet and sour  chicken wings
directions: Salt chicken wings.
Roll in cornstarch.
Dip wings into eggs. Fry until golden brown.
Place wings in oblong deep pan.
Make sauce and pour over chicken wings.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
After 15 minutes cooking, turn wings over.

title: pizza dip
directions: Makes 2 pans.
Layer ingredients in pie pans.
Bake or microwave until melted.
Use as a dip with Wheat Thins.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a large pot brown ground beef and add onions until soft. Add water and bouillon cubes.
Add carrots; cook until carrots are tender.
Add peas.
Thicken with flour and water.
Pour into a baking dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Bake 4 pastry shells and set aside.
Mix other ingredients in a saucepan and cook until heated through.
Spoon into pastry shells and top with chopped parsley.

title: brownie chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9-inch pie pan. Prepare brownie mix for chewy brownies.
Spread evenly on bottom of pan.
Bake 35 minutes until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in well-greased dish (use butter).
Work together sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Pack over apples. If needed, add 2 tablespoons water.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: eight layer vegetable salad
directions: Place ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in the order listed above.

title: peanut brittle
directions: After mixing the ingredients, put on a slow fire and let mixture come to a boil.
Add a piece of paraffin one-inch square; also 1 quart of raw peanuts.
Stir constantly until peanuts are parched.
Take off stove and add 3 teaspoons soda.
Stir just enough to mix well.
Pour out and when firm, break into pieces.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger.
Combine tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, oregano, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Add to hamburger; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown onion, bacon and hamburger.
Add sugars, catsup and mustard.
Drain butter, kidney and green beans.
Do not drain pork and beans.
Mix beans and meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or in crock-pot for 2 hours.
Omit hamburger if this is not a main dish.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 350° for approx 1/2 hour.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash apples; remove core and peel.
Place in deep Pyrex casserole.
In center of each apple, place 1 cube sugar or 1 teaspoon sugar, butter (size of a nut), 1/2 tablespoon jelly of choice and small amount water.
Cook for approximately 1/2 hour at 250°.
Remove from oven; let cool.
Decorate with red jelly.

title: best overnight beef roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over roast.
Roast, covered, at 350° for 3 hours.
Remove meat from drippings.
Cool slightly.
Tightly cover and chill. Put drippings in separate bowl and chill.
The next day, slice beef.
Put meat in a flat roasting pan or lasagne pan.
Skim off fat from drippings and pour over meat.
Reheat, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Excellent and very tender and flavorful.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and butter in mixing bowl.
Sift baking powder and flour together.
Add flour and stir in milk.
Add vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Mix well in mixing bowl.
Spray bottom of deep dish or pan with vegetable cooking spray and pour batter into dish or pan.
Pour peaches on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in shallow 1-quart baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes, until apples are tender and top is browned.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: no-fuss pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides over medium-high heat.
Place in shallow baking pan (not glass), side by side.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over chops evenly.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix juice and grated rind, shortening, water and egg.
Blend liquid into dry ingredients until flour is dampened.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Push into corners and leave center hollow.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: squeekey's nutmeg cutout cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add egg.
Stir in dry ingredients, adding half the flour first, then the yoghurt and then the remaining dry ingredients.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in large mixing bowl.
Place margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan and boil.
When these ingredients reach boiling, add to flour and sugar mix, stirring well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 400° in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour icing over hot cake.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans and flour.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and while cookies are still hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Roll in powdered sugar again when cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in a skillet and drain off fat.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in an uncovered casserole.
Butter beans may be substituted for lima beans.
Add reserved lima bean liquid if needed (just a little).

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, broccoli (thawed), about 1/4 cup onion, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt and pepper to taste. Cook shells (about 24) as directed on the box.
Put a layer of spaghetti sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drain shells and rinse in cold water.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture and place on top of the spaghetti sauce (seam side upright).
Then spread more sauce on top of shells.
Bake at about 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This makes an excellent appetizer, too!
Makes about 20 to 25 shells.

title: pecan glazed pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
In large bowl, using a wire whisk, whisk together eggs, pumpkin, evaporated milk, 3/4 cup sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Place frozen pie crust on preheated baking sheet.
Pour filling into crust.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: raisin-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, vanilla, eggs and 1 teaspoon water in a large mixer bowl; beat until creamy.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir in syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each addition until blended.
Stir in rolled oats.
Pour into pie shell and bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
During baking the oatmeal forms a chewy "nutty" crust on top.
Pie is rich and delicately spiced.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Have margarine at room temperature.
Mix thoroughly with crumbs, peanut butter, vanilla, sugar and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
In double boiler melt wax and stir in chocolate morsels. Dip balls in chocolate and let dry on foil or waxed paper.

title: stuffed cheese bread
directions: Slice off top of sourdough bread. Remove bread from inside sourdough bread. Leave only the hull. Mix all the ingredients and fill the hollow round of bread. Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together; add pineapple with juice, bread pieces and butter.
Mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Now fold in whipped topping.
Place in refrigerator for couple of hours.
Cherries can be used to garnish the top of the salad.

title: fire cracker casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender. Discard drippings. Add chili powder, cumin and salt. Stir well. Cook over low heat 10 minutes. Spoon meat mixture into 13 x 9 baking dish. Layer beans, tortillas and cheese over mixture. Spread soup on top and pour tomatoes and green chilles on top of soup. Cover baking dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: french rice
directions: Combine soup and butter.
Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts, saving liquid. Add water to liquid to make 1 1/3 cups.
Add mushrooms, chestnuts, liquid and rice to soup mixture.
Stir all together.
Pour into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Stir and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of greased casserole. Add celery, then ground beef, onions and pepper. Sprinkle salt/pepper on each layer. Pour tomatoes over mixture in dish and garnish with green pepper rings.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla for 1 1/2 minutes. Add berries and yogurt; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir into batter.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: pocket rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Add shortening, sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Add flour and salt mixture.
Mix well.
Place in covered bowl.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Make out and let rise about 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: melt-in-your mouth dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and baking powder.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Scald milk.
Add margarine, sugar and salt. Cool, then add eggs.
Combine all with flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 2 hours before serving.
Let rise for 2 hours, then bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: house party banana bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar thoroughly; add egg and beat well. Stir in All-Bran, bananas and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture with nutmeats, stirring only until combined.
Spread in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients.
Add soda and hot water last.
Form into rolls and keep in refrigerator or freezer, wrapped in foil or waxed paper.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic together.
Layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish in the order given.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts or you can microwave until cheese melts.

title: epi's salad dressing
directions: Put vinegar, garlic, sugar, salt and mayonnaise in blender. Blend on medium speed and slowly add corn oil in a thin stream. Blend well. Pour into container. Refrigerate remainder.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Spread nuts on a cookie sheet and heat to 325° for 10 minutes. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold in sugar and cinnamon.
After removing nuts from oven, fold into egg mixture. Put the stick of butter on the cookie sheet you toasted the nuts on and put it back into the oven until butter is melted.
Spread the coated nuts onto the cookie sheet with the melted butter and stir, making sure they are well coated.
Bake for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Do not let them get too brown.
Cool thoroughly. Store in a sealed container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine potatoes, 1/3 cup margarine, eggs, sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, coconut and pecans in bowl.
Cut in 1/3 cup margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Refrigerate until just beginning to gel, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Whip Jell-O and Cool Whip together thoroughly.
Stir in with spoon pineapple with juice and mandarin oranges and walnuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and refrigerate.

title: buckeye's
directions: Melt butter.
Add powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
Make into balls and chill for 1/2 hour.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until serving. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan-pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, but pecans.
Put in pie shell and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: aunt fannie's baked squash
directions: Cut up, boil, drain and mash summer squash.
Add 1/2 cup onion, pepper, eggs, 1/2 stick butter, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Put into baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup butter on top and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: winter one dish
directions: Coat beef cubes with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat in oil. Stir in water, tomatoes, barbecue sauce, onions and bay leaf. Bring to rolling boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour until meat is tender. Add carrots, celery and macaroni.
Cover and simmer another 30 or 40 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.

title: josh's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Remove to foil on countertop.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Melt butter; add sugar. Let it melt together. Add the rest of the ingredients. Beat until smooth. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: fresh peach crisp
directions: Arrange peach slices in a baking dish.
Mix sugar and lemon juice and spoon over peaches.
Mix flour, salt and brown sugar. Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: oven crusty fish
directions: Prepare corn flakes; crush into crumbs.
Cut fish into serving pieces about 1/4 pound for each serving.
Combine milk and salt. Dip fish in milk, then in crumbs.
Arrange on well-oiled baking sheet or shallow pan.
Sprinkle fish with oil or melted margarine. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until tender.
Serve with lemon, if desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in buttered baking dish.
Combine the cinnamon, salt and water and sprinkle over apples.
In a separate bowl, mix the flour, brown sugar and butter.
Scatter over top of apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, plain cream or whipped cream.

title: quick summer fruit pie
directions: Spread cookie mix on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cookie crust.

title: steak and onion pie
directions: Cook onions in shortening, remove onions.
Roll meat in flour and seasoning mix.
Brown meat in hot shortening.
Add boiling water, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook 10 minutes. Pour into greased casserole (1 1/2 quart), lay onions on top. Cover with pastry crust rolled 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring butter, milk, chocolate and sugar to a boil in a large saucepan. Boil and stir continuously for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: colonial custard *
directions: Scald milk.
Beat together eggs, salt, vanilla and Grandma's molasses.
Gradually add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Pour into 5 or 6 buttered custard cups.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set custard cups in shallow baking pan; place in oven. Fill pan with hot water to 3/4-inch from top of cups.
Bake in slow oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield: 5 or 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and arrange on pizza pan so that slices are touching (dough placed in the freezer before slicing handles better).
Bake at 350°; cool.

title: mustard vinaigrette
directions: Place mustard in a small bowl.
Add vinegar, tarragon, salt and pepper; whisk well.
Slowly drizzle in the olive oil, whisking constantly, until dressing is creamy.
Makes 1 cup.

title: eve's mushrooms
directions: Wash the mushrooms and slice them thin.
Get the butter very hot in a pan; mix in salt and a little cayenne pepper.
Add the mushrooms.
Cook them briskly for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally; then sprinkle them with the sherry and dill.

title: tallerini
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic in oil.
Add lean hamburger; cook slightly.
Boil noodles.
Add tomatoes, corn and paste to hamburger mixture.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, cheese, celery, ham, pimento and green pepper; add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours.

title: savory cheese soup
directions: In large pan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt; stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.

title: cherry burst pie(icebox)
directions: In medium bowl, combine the sweetened milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in the remaining ingredients (except the pie crust), one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Mound the mixture into the crust.
Freeze for 2 to 3 hours until firm.
Let set at room temperature for 15 or 20 minutes before serving.
I let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If you double recipe, bake 45 minutes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt oleo in dish.
Add the rest and stir up.

title: raisin-bran muffins
directions: Measure Raisin Bran and milk into mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand 2 minutes until softened.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to cereal mix. Stir until well combined.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: bebont homemade pasta
directions: Mix well and let sit for 30 minutes.
Roll in flour, flatten and let sit 2 to 3 hours to dry.
Roll into a long roll and cut 1/4 to 1/2-inch sections.
Place into boiling broth, for instance chicken broth and boneless chicken.
Makes a wonderful chicken noodle soup.

title: overnight salad
directions: Combine lettuce, onion, celery and peas in salad bowl.
Mix well.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar in small bowl.
Spread over salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Chill, tightly covered, for 8 hours or longer.
Top with bacon bits, eggs and cheese.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix in order.
Heat to desired temperature.

title: cowboy chili
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers, celery and jalapenos in a little oil.
Add meat and brown.
Mix in remaining ingredients and add enough water to cover top.
Cook for 3 hours on low heat.
This may be a bit more chili powder than you like.
Taste for seasoning after the first bottle.

title: lasagna maria
directions: Cook lasagna noodles; drain well.
Cook sausage in large skillet until browned; crumble.
Drain.
Stir spaghetti sauce into sausage.
Set aside.
Combine egg and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.

title: cheesy apple pie
directions: In a
mixing bowl, stir together 1 cup flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut in the shortening to the size of small peas.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the water over part of the mixture; toss with a fork.
Repeat until all is moistened.
Form into a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough to form a 12-inch circle.
Ease into 9-inch pie plate.
Trim to 1/2-inch beyond edge of plate; fold under pastry.
Finish edge. Do not prick pastry.
In a bowl, combine apples, sugar, 1/4 cup flour, cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Transfer to crust.
Prepare topping.
Sprinkle over filling.
Cover edge with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes. Remove foil.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes more, until top is golden and fruit is tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add water to make 1 cup and boil to dissolve jello.
Combine pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Mix well and pour 1/2 mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan and let jell.
Spread sour cream over top of mixture.
Pour remaining jello mixture over sour cream and jell until firm.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon; put into a baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours. Yields 6 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Combine, mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate and chill well before serving.

title: sausage, egg and cheese casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cut bread into bite size pieces and layer bottom of dish.
Pour sausage over bread.
Spread cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and salt together and pour over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° next morning for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies(lower cholesterol and saturated fat)
directions: Beat together the oil, egg whites, sugars and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
When it is mixed well, add the chocolate chips.
(This will look and feel a little different than regular dough, but it works.)
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet (Teflon or use spray).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast pull-apart
directions: Preheat oven to
350°. Grease Bundt pan. Arrange frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle
with
dry
butterscotch	pudding mix. Combine brown
sugar
and
cinnamon
and place on rolls.
Add chopped nuts.
Melt butter and pour evenly on top.	Cover with wax	paper and
allow	to raise overnight.
Remove wax paper; bake
at
350° for
minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes and invert on to a serving dish.

title: all american dessert
directions: Dissolve each flavor of gelatin completely in 2 cups boiling water in separate bowls.
Stir 1 cup cold water into each.
Pour into separate 13 x 9-inch pans.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer:
gelatin cubes, whipped topping, cake and strawberries in 3-quart serving bowl.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: May add other spices (I like the Italian spice mix).
Cook 30 to 40 minutes in a 300° to 350° oven.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Lay chicken in bottom of foil-lined baking dish.
Salt, pepper and garlic powder chicken to taste.
Combine soups in saucepan. Mix flour and water and add to soups.
Pour mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and top with herb stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Wine can be added to the soup.
Serve with rice.

title: sherry's shrimp and crabmeat casserole
directions: Toss together all the ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs on top.

title: denny's twinkie cake
directions: Beat the eggs well.
Gradually add the sugar, salt and vanilla to eggs.
Heat the milk and butter to boiling.
Add milk to first mixture and blend.
Add the flour and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, remove from pan.
Slice cake in half horizontally.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and mash well.
Add sour cream, tomato, onion, garlic salt and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Garnish with sprinkles of paprika.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil
the broccoli until tender.
Add mayonnaise, cream of celery
soup,
onion
and
Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Add crumbled
crackers to one stick of melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters and remove hard core.
Place cabbage in boiling salted water, just until limp and easy to roll.

Chop 1 onion and 1/2 bell pepper and set aside to use between layers. While cabbage is cooking, mix uncooked meat, 1 chopped onion, 1/2 chopped bell pepper, 1 can stewed tomatoes, uncooked rice, salt, pepper, sweet basil and picante sauce, if desired.
Mix together very well.
Set aside.
Remove cabbage and let cool.

Place a little of the tomato sauce special in the bottom of a roasting pan. Place about a tablespoon of meat mixture into a cabbage leaf roll and place in the bottom of pan and continue until one layer is complete.
Add a little tomato sauce special and part of the onion and bell pepper you had set aside over the first layer.
Continue with another layer.
Top with small can of tomato sauce.
Add enough water, about 1 1/2 cups to cook.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: barbie cups
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Set aside.
Separate biscuit dough into 12 biscuits.
Place one biscuit in each of 12 ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough up sides to edge.
Spoon mixture into cups.
Sprinkle each with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 2-4-6 bread(yields 4 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve salt and sugar in scalded milk in very large bowl.
Add water, then yeast.
Stir to dissolve yeast.
Add oil, then 5 cups flour; mix.
Continue to add flour until dough is firm but not dry.
You will need to mix it with your hands at the end.
Turn out on floured board and knead for 5 minutes.
Put in greased bowl; grease top of dough.
Put in warm place and let rise about 1 hour until doubled.
Punch down and repeat.
Form into French loaves or put in bread pans.
Bake until golden and sounds hollow when thumped, about 25 to 30 minutes. Brush top with butter.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and marinate overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve 3 or 4 teaspoons of mix to each cup of hot water.

title: spinach loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown bread stuffing; set aside. Mix sour
cream
and onion soup mix
together.	Drain
excess liquid from thawed spinach.
Add spinach to
sour	cream
mixture; mix well.
Pour mixture into well buttered
x 13-inch pan; sprinkle browned bread stuffing over the
top.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken in white wine and cognac
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, brown chicken pieces in hot oil.
When brown, drain off excess oil.
Cut ham into 1/4-inch strips.
Add ham and vegetables to the browned chicken.
Add rest of ingredients except flour, margarine and cognac.
Simmer for 1 hour; remove parsley sprigs and bay leaf.
Cream flour with margarine to blend. Add to mixture and stir until lightly thickened.
Float cognac over the top, light with match, and serve in a ring of rice garnished with mushroom caps.
Serves 6.

title: taco pie
directions: Cover the bottom and
sides
of a 9-inch pie plate with the crescent triangles.
Cook
the onions and pepper with meat until well done.	Add
the
tomato paste, seasoning and water. Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Pour in crust.
Top with cheeses. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: cheese cake(dietetic)
directions: Sprinkle 3 tablespoons crumbs in 9-inch pan; set aside. Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 3/4 cup.
Bring to a boil; stir in gelatin.

title: pesto(6 servings)
directions: Combine ingredients in blender on low; then on medium speed. Thoroughly work into a smooth paste.
Use on spaghetti or vegetables.

title: cajun black-eyed pea stew
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients and cook until peas are tender.
(Do not use iron cookware.)

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken breasts into eggs.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and paprika.
Coat chicken breasts with mixture. Brown chicken (coated) in margarine in heavy skillet.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with mushrooms (optional) and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour Hunt's sauce over all.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, orange
juice and egg until well mixed. In a separate
bowl,
mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Pour the
egg
mixture
into the flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spread
in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350°
until
bread
is
golden
brown and a pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool before storing.

title: red velvet cake
directions: I use 2 tablespoons cocoa and 1 tablespoon Nestle Quik.

title: cabbage in sour cream
directions: Slice carrots in rounds.
Boil until tender but firm in salted water.
Drain and cool.

title: grandma's lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onions and peppers.
Add sauce, tomato paste, oregano and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook noodles according to directions on package. Take bay leaves out of sauce!
Put a little bit of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add layer of noodles, layer of sauce and layer of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is browned as desired.

title: kimmy's cheezy eggs
directions: Beat egg
in
a
bowl.	Break cheese into small pieces. Add to egg.
Microwave for 30 seconds.
Stir.
Cook 10 seconds and stir.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Chops must be thick.
Cut pockets lengthwise through center to bone for the stuffing.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stuff with sweet potatoes, apples, salt, pepper and egg.
Fasten the edges with toothpicks.
Dip in milk and roll in bread crumbs. Bake in a greased pan for 1 1/2 hours or until tender at 350°.

title: "amish" friendship bread
directions: Mix
well and put into 2 large greased and sugared loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon crackle cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugars. Add the egg and extracts; mix well. Combine the next 8 ingredients. Gradually add to the creamed mixture. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Yields about 6 dozen.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix with electric mixer.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix cheeses together. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs, milk and flour together. Pour over cheese. Sprinkle peppers on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cut into squares. Good hot or cold.

title: easy pie
directions: Mix together the Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with a fruit filling.

title: chili casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet. Add chili powder, salt and oregano. Stir in beans and tomatoes. Remove from heat.
Spoon half of the beef mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half the cheese (save 1/2 cup for topping).
Top with half of the tortilla chips.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with saved cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese has melted and mixture is bubbly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Defrost your broccoli.
Roast or broil your chicken.
Remove all meat from the bones.
Mix all the ingredients together except for the breadcrumbs and the butter pats.
Place your casserole in a dish.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs all over the top, covering well. Add the butter pats on top.
Bake at 350° in an oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Layer first four ingredients in order listed in crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layers.
Do not stir.
