Cook 2 to 3 hours on high or 8 hours on low.
Stir before serving.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Braise chicken cutlets in margarine.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Cover with mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Add chicken gravy.
Bake covered in 350° oven until gravy bubbles.
Serves 4.

title: artichoke hearts pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread over pita bread.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into pie-shape portions.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mash cream cheese and add flavor and color; then mix in sugar, finally kneading with the hands until about like pie dough.
Roll in balls about the size of marbles.
Place one side in a small amount of sugar; then press sugar side down in molds.
Unmold at once on waxed paper.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend with mixer and serve with apple slices.
Also good with any fresh fruit.

title: three pepper chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except vinegar and chicken, in a saucepan.
Heat until sugar and salt is dissolved.
Cool; add vinegar and process in the blender.
Spread over chicken in a pan or bowl, coating well.
Marinate at least 4 hours in refrigerator before grilling.
Remove chicken, drain back into bowl.
Grill 40 to 50 minutes.
Baste with reserved marinade another 20 minutes until done.

title: summer salad
directions: Fix jello in flat dish.
Put in refrigerator until jelled. Cut into cubes and mix with other ingredients; chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: With all ingredients at room temperature, mix, shape and store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bananas.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add cold water.
Stir well.
Let chill until slightly thickened.
Break up cranberry sauce with a fork.
Stir into gelatin with celery and nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into oiled 1-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: mother's chocolate caramels
directions: Mix all ingredients except walnuts and cook until it will form a ball in cold water.
Pour in buttered pan and sprinkle with pecans or nuts.
When cool, cut in 1/2-inch squares and roll in wax paper.

title: chili verde(green chili)
directions: Melt margarine in emptied roast pan.
Dredge roast pieces in flour.
Drop roast and extra flour into hot margarine; cook until brown.
Stir often, scraping bottom of pan to avoid burning flour.

title: rigatoni and meat sauce
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, combine ground beef, onion and garlic.
Cook until ground beef is no longer pink; drain if necessary.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Prepare rigatoni according to package directions; drain.
Serve with meat sauce. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onion together. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Cover cream cheese mixture with taco sauce (strength depends on individual taste).
Shred a layer of lettuce next, then add green pepper, tomato and cheese (each in layers).
Finish up with black olives that are sliced. Chill.
Serve with taco chips.

title: stuffed franks 'n taters
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In large bowl, combine potatoes, soup, 1/2 French-fried onions, sour cream and seasonings.
Spread potato mixture in 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Split frankfurters lengthwise, almost into halves. Arrange frankfurters, split side up, along center of casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Fill frankfurter with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 1 to 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown. Yield: 6 servings.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Mix milk and oil together, then add dry ingredients to make a soft ball.
Drop by spoonfuls in broth.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not lift cover.
Use in any kind of broth.

title: smoky surprise burgers
directions: Mix beef, salt and pepper.
Divide mixture into quarters. Then divide each quarter in half.
Pat each portion out on a sheet of waxed paper to 4 1/2 inches.
Combine barbecue sauce, mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread 4 of the patties with this mixture, dividing the mixture among them.
Top each of the sauced patties with a slice of Cheddar cheese and a slice of Swiss cheese.
Cover filled patties with remaining patties, pinching edges to seal well.
Broil 6 to 8 minutes using a broiling pan or a charcoal grill.
Then serve immediately.

title: oatmeal cookies (4)
directions: Beat spry, eggs, and sugars well with a mixer.	Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Add pineapple, oranges and pecans. Mix well. Pour into a dish and chill. Top with pecans and orange slices. Keeps well.

title: vinegar roll (aunt jo's)(serves 8)
directions: Mix vinegar, water and 2 cups sugar; bring to boil.
Roll pie dough thin and oblong.
Spread generously with soft margarine; sprinkle with 1 cup remaining sugar.
Roll up as for jelly roll, beginning on long side.
Cut crosswise slices 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Place cut side down in baking pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Slice remaining margarine over rolls.
Pour hot sugar and vinegar mixture over rolls.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Liquid will be creamy and thick.
This is an old ranch country recipe; used when fresh fruit was unavailable.

title: apple crumb loaf
directions: Quarter, core and peel apples.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Spread evenly on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until apples are tender but not mushy.
Remove from pan and cool.
Beat 1/2 cup margarine until creamy; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream.
Sift together 2 cups flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Fold into margarine.
Add apples, folding in gently.
Pour half of the mixture into a greased, wax paper lined and greased again 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Cut remaining margarine into remaining flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until crumblike.
Sprinkle half of the crumb mixture over the batter; pour in remaining batter.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until browned, pulled away from the edges and a toothpick inserted near center has no sticky dough adhering to it.
Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes. Carefully remove from pan.

title: cherry-pineapple cake
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread the pineapple and cherry pie filling in pan. Sprinkle 1 package of dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt cube of butter or margarine and pour over cake.
Mix.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Spread Cool Whip over cake when cool.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple sandwich spread
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Add lemon juice.
Mix flour in pineapple juice; add to pineapple.
Cook until thick. Cool before spreading.
Spread mayonnaise on one side and pineapple on the other side.
Softened cream cheese may be substituted for mayonnaise.

title: gooey, chewy popcorn balls
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels from popcorn.
Melt margarine, caramels and marshmallows in a large pan.
Put popped corn in a large bowl or plastic container.
Pour melted caramel mixture over popcorn and mix.
Butter hands and shape popcorn into balls. Place on waxed paper to cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature to soften. Beat cream cheese with mixer until fluffy. Add sugar and vanilla; blend well. Add eggs one at a time and blend. Add sour cream; blend. Spread in graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cut apples into small chunks. Add sugar, salt and margarine in saucepan. Cook until apples are tender.
Roll biscuits out to 1/4-inch thick.
Place apple mixture on 1 side of biscuit. Fold over and press edges with fork. Fry in greased skillet until brown.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and pepper.
Drain mushrooms.
Fold in chicken, mushrooms and green onions.
Roll out rolls and place 1/4 cup mixture in each; roll up.
Seal edges. Dip into melted butter and roll in bread crumbs mixed with chopped nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with gravy.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Peel orange and cut the skin into very fine julienne.
Set aside.
Squeeze both oranges for juice; set aside.
Combine sugar and lemon juice in small saucepan.
Heat slowly until sugar begins to caramelize.
If necessary, wash down sides of pan by brushing with water.
When sugar is caramel colored, add the julienne ginger and orange peel.
Cook 1 minute, add the cranberries, orange juice and pepper.
Cook on medium-high heat, stirring frequently for about 5 minutes (or 7 minutes for frozen cranberries).
Remove from heat, let cool.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Cut carrots (approximately 6) into 2 x 1/4-inch strips. Slice celery and set aside.
Heat oil in wok or skillet until hot. Add carrots and celery and stir-fry over medium heat for about 10 minutes or until almost tender.
Add onion and
zucchini and continue stirring until crisp and tender.
Add seasonings and serve.

title: cracker dressing
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish with Pam.
Spread mixture in dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown and crusty on top.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, flour, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt and spread in a greased pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Mix together remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of rhubarb mixture. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over top.
Bake in a 375° oven until bubbly and light brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange mandarin cake
directions: Use two 9-inch cake pans, lightly greased and floured.
Stir cake mix, mandarin oranges and juice, eggs and oil together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Be sure to let cake cool completely before frosting.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Microwave melted butter, onion and broccoli until soft, almost done.
Add eggs to cornbread mix and mix; add rest of ingredients and mix until blended.
Pour into greased pan or casserole dish. Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water, corn syrup and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Stir in blueberries.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce comes to a boil and is thickened. Yields about 1 3/4 cup.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine all except cheese and Doritos in a large mixing bowl. Once mixed (with a wooden spoon), prepare Doritos in a 10 x 13-inch baking pan by spreading a small layer on the bottom. Spread meat mixture on top of Doritos and spread cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: holiday jello salad *
directions: Mix Jell-O and liquid.
Chill until syrupy.
Mix softened cream cheese and stir in whipped cream.
Fold in other ingredients.
Add to Jell-O.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: the magic pickle
directions: Drain the pickles. While they are draining, put the pickling spices and vinegar into a clean half gallon jar. Add drained pickles, and pour sugar on top of them. Do not stir.

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in saucepan. Add coconut. Saute until just golden brown, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Cream remaining butter. Add cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk.
Beat after each addition. Add vanilla and 1 cup sauteed coconut. Spread on cake. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Will ice a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: kielbasa bean bake
directions: Remove casing from kielbasa (optional).
Use a bean pot or any type of casserole.
I use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Prepare dirty rice mix according to package directions; cut cooking time in half.
Season with salt and pepper and brown sirloin in skillet.
In a pot, add chicken broth, water, tomato soup, stewed tomatoes, peppers, onions and canadian bacon and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to a simmer and add 2 cups of cooked rice mix and browned sirloin.
Cook 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat
eggs
and
add remaining ingredients; pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: carrot surprise salad
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate 24 hours. Serve cold.
Delicious!

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda and spices.
Mix well. Stir in oats, dried fruit and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 375°.
Cool one minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack. Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Season chicken and boil until done.
Remove chicken from broth and set aside until cool, then debone.
Add noodles to broth and cook according to package directions.
Drain, reserving one cup broth.
Set aside.

title: okroshka
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly; chill.
Serve with kvas or beer.

title: chocolate chip nut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 18 muffins cups or line with paper baking cups.
In small bowl, combine 1/4 cup flour, brown sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend with fork until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Blend well.
Add sour cream, 1/2 cup butter, milk, vanilla and egg; stir just until moistened.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full; sprinkle each with streusel.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 18.

title: sweet and sour broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Bring to a boil while stirring the mayonnaise, oil, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables and bacon.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and debone the chicken.
Mix all the ingredients listed and add salt and pepper.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Beat margarine or butter in a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar and beat until well combined.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add the flour mixture to the beaten mixture.
Beat at low speed just until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and 1 cup walnuts.
Spread batter in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: coconut pie (no crust)
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add flour and mix.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs; mix.
Add coconut (I add until mixture is thick, just guess).
Pour into 2 well creased pie platters (I grease mine with margarine).
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil. Set aside.
Using a large mixing bowl, mix well the sugar, flour, buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and pinch of salt.
Add the hot mixture to this and mix again well.
Add the marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot artichoke crabmeat dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add garlic. Add artichokes, crabmeat, Parmesan cheese, green onions, lemon zest and black pepper. Mix well.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots and onion together until just tender.
Do not overcook.
Gently stir in the margarine, cheese and mayonnaise. Put mixture into casserole dish.
Top with about 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: If ribs are fatty, bake with no sauce for 3/4 hour, then pour off fat before adding sauce.
Mix together remaining ingredients. (For quicker cooking, you may heat the sauce to boiling before pouring over ribs.)
Pour sauce over ribs in deep pan or roaster.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 2 hours (or 1 1/4 hours if already removed fat).

title: jello salad or dessert
directions: Heat nectar to boiling point and add jello to dissolve. Add lemon
juice
and pineapple.
Cool.
Add bananas and chill to firm.
Put	mayonnaise
on	for
salad or whipped cream for dessert.

title: macaroni with sausage and peppers
directions: Skin sausage, crumble and cook with green peppers in oil until sausage is lightly browned.
Pour off excess oil.
Add spaghetti sauce, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Toss sauce with macaroni.

title: lisa west's pudding pops
directions: Prepare pudding according to package instructions.
Sweeten to taste.
Pour into popsicle mold and freeze for at least 1 hour. Serving number depends on size of popsicle holder.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll in chopped walnuts or pecans.

title: frosting
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer for 20 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 or 3 weeks.

title: luscious lemon chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat. Add remaining
ingredients
except lemon slices.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally. Chill overnight.	Reheat	in
covered skillet about 15 minutes or until hot.
Stir and garnish with lemon.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: *You may substitute other cake/Jell-O flavors.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, mustard and onion together.
Spread sauerkraut in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Cover with sausage pieces and sprinkle with cheese. Stir melted butter and crumbs together; put over cheese layer.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients and bake for 1 hour or until center is done.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: shrimp rice dinner
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni following directions on box.
When finished, add shrimp and artichokes hearts (with juice).
Serve hot or cold.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine and shortening in water with cocoa and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixed with sugar.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix. Will make very thin batter.
Bake at 400° in long pan for 25 minutes.
Start frosting 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown meat first.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high heat until steaming, then simmer 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate sin cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pan liberally.
Line the bottom with wax paper and butter the paper.
Preheat oven to 350°. In top of double boiler, melt the chocolate over hot water.
Add the butter and stir until the butter has melted and the mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Whisk the sugar gradually into the chocolate mixture until smooth.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs until foamy.
Then stir into chocolate mixture.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on the box. Boil large can of pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes or until thick. Pour over warm cake and cool. Cut up bananas and place over pineapple. Mix the pudding according to directions on box and spread over bananas. Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Top with coconut, chopped nuts and cherries.

title: pistachio salad
directions: This recipe can be doubled.
Mix all ingredients together. Drain fruit well.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour, then serve.

title: bean bake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry or strawberry crunch
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of 8 x 12-inch oblong dish or pan and smooth out.
Add pineapple on top of filling, then sprinkle sugar.
Smooth dry cake mix on top and pour melted margarine on top of dry cake mix, then add chopped pecans.
Smooth out all layers and cook for 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In ungreased, 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix pie filling and almond extract.
Heat in oven about 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
In small bowl, mix baking mix, sugar, milk and margarine with fork until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Stir in toasted almonds.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto hot cherry mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is light brown.
Serve.

title: orange torte cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Fold in dates, raisins, nuts and orange rind.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted is clean, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: herbed pot roast
directions: Brown meat well in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until meat is fork-tender.
Make gravy with drippings.
Serves 4.

title: pasta vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour dressing over mixture. Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Precook chicken by boiling for 45 minutes for whole chicken or 1/2 hour for breast pieces.
Drain and debone; set aside.

title: jollof rice
directions: Boil stew beef for 15 to 20 minutes until tender (2 cups of water to a pound of beef).
Heat cooking oil for about 2 minutes. Place boiled meat into heated oil; fry for 1 minute.
Add onion; fry until onion becomes brown.
Add tomato sauce; cook for another 5 minutes.
Add 4 cups of water to the "gravy" now prepared.
Boil everything for about 10 minutes.
Add rice to gravy; cook for 20 to 25 minutes on low until Jollof Rice is tender.
Ready to serve.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and mix well, then add sour cream.
Next, combine flour, soda and cream of tartar; add to egg mixture, stirring in a little at a time.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over Nabisco bran.
Let stand while sifting together the flour, soda and salt.
Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs, buttermilk and All-Bran.
Mix all together until moistened and place in covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps good for 6 weeks.
Delicious.

title: ranch flavored pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into small pieces.
Add oil to coat pretzels. Add dill weed, lemon pepper and Ranch dip.
Mix well.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: lava dip
directions: Layer 1:
Spread over bottom of 9 1/2 x 11 1/2 baking dish, 2 cans jalapeno bean dip.

title: "bologna" candy
directions: Name derived from the way candy is dried and the way it is cut for serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients until moist.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl often.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Put one teaspoon of mix to cup of hot water.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix
flour,
shortening
and sugar.
Then mix yeast and warm water
separately
and
add to mixture.
Roll out and cut like biscuits.
Then fold over when putting in pan.
(Let rise only once.) After they have risen, bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 400° to 450° or until brown, then brush with melted margarine.
Makes about 12 large rolls.

title: brisket(we eat this every year at hanukkah.)
directions: Line a large roasting pan with heavy foil, letting the ends of the foil hang over the edges of the pan.
Place brisket in the pan.
Sprinkle sugar, soup mix and garlic powder over brisket. Drizzle catsup all over.
Fold ends of foil over brisket, sealing securely and leaving air space.
Bake 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender at 325°.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Chop onion and saute with beef.
Cook macaroni.
When beef and onion are done, add tomato soup, milk and cheese slices.
Stir until well blended.
Drain macaroni and add to beef mixture; stir.
Place into a casserole dish and top with the 2 slices of bread, crumbled up.
Brown the bread.
If mixture is dry, add a little more milk.

title: apple salad
directions: In medium bowl combine apples, pineapple, raisins, pecans and whipped topping.
Mix well and serve chilled.

title: sparkling lemonade
directions: Prechill 1 quart pitcher and four 12 ounce glasses.
Combine sugar and lemon juice in chilled pitcher, stirring every 5 minutes until sugar is completely dissolved.
To serve, add club soda to syrup.
Syrup mixture can be made ahead and refrigerated for 3 days.

title: party ryes
directions: Brown mild and hot sausages together; drain grease. Add cubed Velveeta cheese to meat.
Cook on low fire until cheese is melted. Spread by spoonful onto party rye.
These can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Heat in microwave or oven to serve.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt cheese and butter slowly in medium pot.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until mixture is creamy.
Fold egg whites into cheese mixture.
Cut crust off bread slices.
Cut each slice of bread into 4 squares.
Stack the 4 squares on top of each other, then spread cheese mixture between the layers.
Spread the mixture over the outside of the stack, like frosting a cake. Place each stack 1/2 inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Delicious!

title: baked beans
directions: Brown
hamburger and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water; stir until dissolved.
Melt margarine; cool to lukewarm.
Add margarine, eggs and sugar to water mixture.
Add flour; beat until smooth.
Dough wil be the consistency of waffle batter.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Batter will keep about a week in refrigerator.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray pan with vegetable spray.
Layer the coconut and pecans. Press into bottom of pan.
Mix the cake mix by directions on box; pour over first layer.
Melt the oleo.
Add the sifted powdered sugar and cream cheese; mix well.
Pour over cake; do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.
(Do not overbake.)

title: stuffed sparerib
directions: Sprinkle ribs with pepper.
Place stuffing into rib.
Roll rib and tie with string.
Spread butter over rib; sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap in foil and put in baking pan.
Bake at 400° to 425° until done.
Open foil to brown.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In a large Teflon-coated pan, melt marshmallows in milk.
In a separate large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
When marshmallow mixture is smooth, stir into ingredients in bowl and mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: applesauce-oat muffins
directions: Place Cheerios in large Ziploc bag.
Crush with rolling pin (a great kid job!).
Combine with flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda in large bowl.
Stir in applesauce, milk, raisins and oil and egg white.
Blend until moistened.
Grease bottoms of 12 muffin cups.
Fill evenly.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 22 minutes until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into lightly greased (spray with vegetable oil spray) Bundt pan.
Place, uncovered, in microwave.
Cook 10 minutes on 50% power or cook 10 minutes on 100% power.
Let stand 10 minutes before inverting on serving platter.
Can frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: best brownies ever
directions: Stir in order:
margarine, cocoa, sugar, eggs (all at once), flour, vanilla, chocolate chunks and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cool, peel and grate.
Add all ingredients, except corn flakes, and place in a greased casserole dish.
Put corn flakes on top; drizzle with a little melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Cook onion in shortening until almost tender.
Add meat and salt.
Then add pepper and chili powder.
Stir until well blended. Place in a well greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place potatoes in a layer over meat; add a layer of beans and a layer of corn.
Sprinkle each layer lightly with a layer of corn.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with sugar.
Add cheese and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fricassee rabbit
directions: Let rabbit pieces stand in vinegar brine for 3 hours.
Drain, dry and sprinkle m.s.g. evenly on all pieces.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix seasonings and sprinkle on meat. Brown in fat or oil.
Put onion in casserole.
Arrange rabbit on top.
Combine vinegar and water and pour over rabbit pieces. Cover and bake at 275° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: pina colada
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.

title: zesty vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: mama's thwack biscuits
directions: Take 1 roll of biscuits; thwack hard on edge of counter.
Bake as directed on package.
Serve piping hot.
Enjoy!

title: chicken dijon
directions: Mix together the butter, mustard and garlic. Set aside. Mix together the crumbs, cheese and parsley. Set aside. Wash and dry breasts. Dip both sides of each half of breasts in mustard mixture. Dip one side only in crumb mixture. Place on baking sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 500°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat again.
Add salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add flour.
Blend thoroughly.
Add zucchini.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Stir together and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt. Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight if you wish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
May add mushrooms.

title: helen's salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a large container and shake well.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten crescent roll dough in a pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, milk and mayonnaise; spread on crust.
Sprinkle on about 1 package of Ranch style dry dressing.
Chop fine whatever vegetables you like, such as broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, peppers or onion.
Press onto cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Dredge one side of bacon strip in cheese.
With cheese side out, roll bacon around bread stick diagonally.
Place sticks on microwave dish or paper plate lined with paper towels.
Microwave on High 4 1/2 to 6 minutes.
When done, roll again in cheese.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: May cook on top of stove or bake in oven until juice is cooked in.

title: overnight salad
directions: Break up lettuce and cauliflower into covered container.
Put in chopped onion and fried bacon.
Add Miracle Whip; do not stir. Sprinkle a little sugar onto the ingredients.
Let set overnight or several hours, covered tightly.
Stir all the ingredients before serving.

title: dill weed vegetable dip
directions: Hellmann's is the best mayonnaise to use.
Mix all ingredients.
Use for all fresh vegetables.

title: broccoli-mushroom salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Sprinkle dry dressing over, then liquid dressing.
Toss and marinate overnight.

title: stuffed giant shells
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and garlic until crumbly.
Drain excess fat and cool.
Stir in cheese, parsley, bread crumbs and egg.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook shells in boiling salt water until almost tender (approximately 15 minutes).
Drain and stuff with meat mixture.
Spoon 1/4 of sauce into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Put in stuffed shells, side by side.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Serve with more Parmesan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Both of these recipes are favorites at family gatherings or to take as a covered dish.

title: guacamole
directions: In a medium bowl, mash avocados coarsely with a fork. Stir in tomato, lime juice, onion, salt and hot sauce.
Mix well. Add black pepper to taste. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours.
Garnish with additional chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: nacho salad
directions: Arrange nacho chips around outer edge of salad.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, white Karo and melted butter.
Add well beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Place layer of
cake
in
bottom
of bowl, then a layer each of
pudding,
pineapple (sprinkle over), cherry pie filling, coconut
(sprinkle
over),
blueberry
pie
filling, nuts (sprinkle over) and fruit cocktail.
Put Cool Whip on top with a few cherries.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon sugar with cinnamon; set aside.
In small bowl, beat remaining sugar with egg, vanilla and salt until very thick and fluffy.
Stir together flour and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture until well blended, then stir in reserved juice. Pour into well-greased 8-inch layer cake pan.
Arrange peach slices on top.
Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 375°
for 25 to 30 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 5 minutes.
Unmold and invert.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, spices, salt, pumpkin, molasses and evaporated milk.
Stir with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth.
Lightly brush pie shell with egg white.
Fill with pumpkin mixture.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until top of sharp knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool on wire rack.
Serve garnished with whipped cream, if desired.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients thoroughly with pastry blender until coarse crumb consistency.
Take out 1 cup; reserve for topping.
To remaining mixture, add the eggs and milk.
After blending, fold in the blueberries, which have been dusted with sugar-cinnamon mixture to coat.
Pour into two 8-inch round cake pans; sprinkle the reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Freezes well.)

title: new year's punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix Southern Comfort, lemon juice, lemonade and orange juice in punch bowl; add 7-Up.
Add drops of red food coloring.
Float frozen bunches of grapes and orange slices. Yield:
32 servings.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Put 1/2 grated cheese in ungreased baking dish (7 x 9-inches or 8 x 12-inches).
Beat eggs; spread over cheese with spatula. Sprinkle picante sauce over this.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let set up for about 5 minutes; cut into squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand about 1 hour.
Separate eggs.
Beat whites stiff.
Add yolk and Crisco oil.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Pour egg mixture over apples.
Add dry ingredients and nuts; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 60 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: rouladen
directions: Cut steak into 4 pieces.
Pound until paper thin.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook bacon in skillet until done, but not crisp. Place two slices of bacon on each piece of meat, long way on meat. Add one tablespoon of bread crumbs to each piece of meat.
Place pickle across short side of meat and roll up.
Pickle is center. Secure.
Place in bacon grease; brown on all sides.
Reduce heat; add 1/4 cup water and simmer for 30 minutes, covered.

title: fruit bars
directions: In a saucepan, heat raisins, sugar, water, oleo, salt and spices until boiling.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes, then add flour and baking soda.
Spread on a cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and spread on a thin glaze of powdered sugar and milk.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco.
Add sugar gradually while creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan which has been well-greased.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish (flat glass dish).
Add crumbs.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and milk together; pour over crumbs. Slice bananas over cream cheese mixture, then add pineapple (using juice).
Top with nuts and cherries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Combine mayonnaise and mustard; spread over cauliflower.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: sliced green tomato crisp pickle
directions: Mix lime and water well, letting any lime that does not dissolve settle to bottom.
Select, wash, dry and slice tomatoes. Pour off lime water and add sliced tomatoes to it.
Soak 24 hours, then wash each piece well under running water and dry.
Mix sugar and vinegar and pour over tomatoes.
Soak 12 hours.
Add spices and bring to boil.
Cook at that point for 30 minutes.
Place in churn or glass jars.
This will keep unsealed.
Yields approximately 8 pints.
(Worth the effort.)

title: deviled eggs
directions: Wrap chicken livers, mammoth stuffed olives, mushrooms and pineapple chunks all with narrow strips of bacon.
Broil until the bacon is crisp, or bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour and mix in Rice Krispies and red pepper.
Make into small balls and press with fork crosswise.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, cook oil until hot.
Add pork chops and onions.
Cook until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and water mixture.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer on low until pork chops are done and are fork-tender. Stir occasionally while cooking.
Serve with rice or baked potato.

title: frosty grapes
directions: Divide grapes into small bunches.
Rinse grapes and drain in colander or strainer to remove excess water.
Put gelatin in a container with a lid.
Add grapes to the container and shake to coat grapes lightly with gelatin.
Shake off excess gelatin from grape bunches.
Put lid back on container and freeze.
Serve as a dessert, snack or garnish for main dish or salad.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix well first 2 ingredients.
Boil in pot the next 3 ingredients.
Pour cocoa mixture into flour and sugar mixture. Mix well.
Mix last 2 ingredients into cocoa and flour mixture. Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes in 400° oven. Frost right in pan.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package, adding 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan, according to package directions. When cake is removed from oven, punch holes at 1-inch intervals with fork.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice to water to make 3 1/2 cups.
Remove cranberry sauce from can and cut into tiny cubes.
Heat the juice and water with jello to dissolve.
Chill until a little thickened. Add remaining ingredients; pour into mold and chill.

title: quick and easy apple pie
directions: Layer peeled and sliced apples on bottom of 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the apples.
Mix by hand the flour and butter until the mixture holds together.
Shape pieces of pastry in hands and lay on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and yogurt quickly.
(Let thaw enough for mixing.)
Using a medium sized pan with top, layer cookies and cream mixture until you have several layers of each.
For beauty cut maraschino cherries and place on top.
Freeze and serve in blocks.

title: aunt nettie deason's meat loaf
directions: Soak cracker crumbs in milk.
Add eggs.
Add to meat.
Form into small loaves and bake in greased pans at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. You can use catsup or mustard on top of meat loaves.
You may use this to make meat balls for spaghetti.
Just form balls and roll in seasoned flour and fry.
Add to spaghetti sauce.

title: pink fluff
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix ingredients (except coconut).
Chill and serve in a pretty glass bowl.
Sprinkle with coconut before serving.
This dish may be poured in a 13 x 9-inch pan, frozen, then cut in squares and served on a lettuce leaf, also.
This dish may be served as a salad or dessert.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Saute broccoli, onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until broccoli is crisp.
Add sherry, butter, salt, basil and flour. Mix and melt.
Add chicken broth.
Stir in mushrooms and simmer 15 minutes.
Add half and half and warm to serve.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: scones
directions: Sieve flour, salt and soda in large bowl.
Cut in butter and mix well.
Add sugar and egg (beaten).
Mix to soft dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead lightly a few times and roll out, then cut into 2-inch rounds.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine the flour, salt, soda, sugar and cinnamon; stir in pecans. Combine the eggs, vegetable oil, bananas, pineapple and vanilla. Add to the flour mixture, stirring just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Spread batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.

title: orange date syrup
directions: Dissolve
arrowroot in 1/4 cup water.
Pour into saucepan with
remaining
water and dates.
Simmer until liquid is thick and clear and dates are soft.
Pour into blender.
Blend smooth. Add juice and blend slightly.
Serve.
Makes 2 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese and chicken(frankie's favorite)
directions: Cook
macaroni until tender;
drain and rinse with cold water. Cut
chicken into bite size pieces; cook in skillet on medium heat.
Use 1/4 cup oil.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: biscuits
directions: Measure flour into bowl.
Mix oil and milk together; mix into flour until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead on lightly floured surface.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 500° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tart apple pie
directions: Cut margarine into flour until pea size.
Add beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Mix lightly with fork until forms a ball.
Let dough rest 10 minutes.
For this apple pie, roll out on well floured board 1/4 of the dough and place in 9-inch pie tin.
Fill with the fruit mixture below.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, egg yolks, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into pie shell. Top with stiffly beaten egg whites, sweetened to taste.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine
drained
vegetables, soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, pepper
and
of
the onions.
Pour into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole with cover.
Bake, covered, at 350° for
30 minutes.
Top
with
remaining
cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Microwave bacon 4 minutes or until crisp.
Remove and crumble. Save drippings in pie plate.
Spread potatoes in pie plate and microwave 6 to 7 minutes on High.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave 6 to 7 minutes, turning every 3 minutes 1/4 turn. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Cover and microwave 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes, then cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy, delicious baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken; place in small roaster.
Sprinkle with poultry seasoning and garlic powder to taste.
Pour soy sauce all over. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together; chill and serve in hollowed French bread.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients. Add other ingredients in order and mix thoroughly. Bake in 2 greased and floured 8 inch cake pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, beat Eagle Brand condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.
Press Hershey's Kiss in center of each ball immediately after baking.
Cool.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.
Remove foil from Kiss before pressing into cookie.

title: pace chili-chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil in Dutch oven until chicken loses its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 20 minutes. Ladle into bowls.
Top with cheese, onion, sour cream and additional picante sauce as desired.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in casserole dish.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise together and place on top of vegetables.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Put on top of casserole; bake at 350° until bubbles or done.

title: baked apple pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Grease 10 x 15 baking sheet. Whisk all ingredients, except apples.
Fold in apples and pour on baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown. Cut into squares. Serve with syrup or fruit sauce.

title: mustard french dressing
directions: Beat the mustard and egg white in a bowl for a good minute with a wire whip.
When thick, beat in the lemon juice or vinegar and the salt. Then, by droplets, beat in the oil to make a cream sauce.
Beat in the optional ingredients and correct the seasoning.
This dressing is lightly thickened, for about 1/2 cup.

title: peppers and steak
directions: Cut steak into thin slices.
Place half the steak in crock-pot.
Arrange peppers on steak.
Place remaining steak on top of peppers.
(Mushrooms can be added at this time.)
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours, on high setting for 3 to 4 hours. During last hour of cooking, stock may be thickened, if desired. Serve over bed of hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Wash and core the peppers.
Mix the cheeses together and stuff the peppers.
Wrap enough sausage around the pepper to cover it. Roll the pepper in the Shake 'n Bake.
Bake at 425° until the sausage is done.
Will make approximately 12 peppers.

title: cheesy football
directions: Beat cheeses and mayonnaise with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add onions and pepper; mix well. Cover. Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Form into football shape. Cover with bacon bits. Add pimento strips to form "lacing" for "football."
Serve with Ritz crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop beef.
Mix 1/2 chipped beef with remaining ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Roll ball in remaining chipped beef.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and wait about 15 minutes; then turn out of pan.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix ingredients together; place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: baked egg dish
directions: Beat eggs and half and half.
Cook on top of stove.
Choose your favorite breakfast meat (ham, sausage or bacon) and cook.
Put eggs in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread meat on top of eggs.
Put mushroom soup on top of meat.
Add cheese on top.
Cover and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cuts best if you let it set after baking.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: From one medium size watermelon,
trim	rind, leaving a pink edge for color.
Cut the rind
into small squares (1 to 1 1/4 inches).
Make a brine of 1 cup salt to 1 gallon water and soak rind overnight.

title: new potatoes and peas
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, cook potatoes about 8 minutes, or until fork-tender; drain in colander.
In same saucepan, combine soup, milk, dill weed and pepper.
Add potatoes and peas with onions.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with fresh dill and lemon wedge.

title: french lemon pie
directions: Beat
eggs
and add vanilla.
Mix sugar in flour.
Melt butter and
add syrup and lemon.
Mix everything together and pour into raw pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter/margarine in a saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Pour over popped corn and mix thoroughly.
Place in large uncovered pan (about 18 x 12 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake in low oven (200°) for 1 hour.
Remove and spread on waxed paper or foil and separate into bite sized pieces.
Store in covered container.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Add Cool Whip, sour cream and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix together.
Chop bananas and add to mixture or slice and put over a layer on vanilla wafers.
Pour mixture into dish and put another layer of wafers.

title: surprize cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and roll thin.
Cut into 3-inch circles.
Place 1/2 of the cookies on greased sheet.
Mix together the remaining ingredients for a filling and cook until thick. Stir carefully as this burns quickly.
Put 1 teaspoon filling on cookies; top with second cookie.
Press edges with a fork.
Don't let filling reach edges.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poo poo's
directions: Have your mom or dad toast coconut flakes in the oven at 350° until brown.
Cut your banana into bite-size pieces.
Dip into your favorite yogurt and roll in toasted coconut.
Wala Poo Poo's.
Serves as many as you like.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all but 1 cup pecans; roll ball in remaining 1 cup pecans.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups liquid. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add reserved liquid.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cherries, lemon peel, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into pastry shell. Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and spices.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over cherries.
Bake in a 400° oven about 30 minutes or until crust is brown. Serve warm.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Blend together in blender. Add 1 c. Cool whip. Chill for about 4 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine corn (fresh corn cut from cob is best, but canned corn will do fine) in bowl with beaten eggs. Sift in dry ingredients and beat slightly until smooth. Drop by spoonfuls onto hot, well-greased skillet, turning each fritter to brown well on each side.

title: west of the pecos enchiladas
directions: Brown the beef.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and garlic salt. Reserve 1 cup cheese.
Add meat to remaining cheese, olives and onions.
Combine tomato sauce, tomato paste, soup, water, oil, chili powder, garlic powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Simmer.
Dip tortilla in sauce; place a heaping tablespoon of meat in center. Roll.
Lay filled tortillas in baking dish.
Pour 1 cup sauce over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat fat.
Stir and fry onions lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat about 50 minutes.
Serve with any cooked meat except fowl.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put pickles in jars.
Heat mixture to a rolling boil.
Pour into jars.
Boil rings and lids to help lids seal.
Screw rings firmly on the jars.

title: el gando
directions: Cook ground beef until particles separate. Add garlic salt, chili mix and tomatoes. Simmer until almost dry. Cook rice as directed on package. Put a layer of meat and tomato mixture in a large serving dish. Add a layer of rice on meat mixture. Add the remainder of the tomatoes and meat mixture. Heat can of soup and milk and spread over meat mixture. Sprinkle olives, onions, cheese and Fritos over mixture. Garnish with lettuce and tomato wedges.

title: angie's asparagus roll-ups
directions: Trim crust off bread.
Spread soup on bread.
Take 1 piece of asparagus from can and roll up in bread.
Brush with melted butter.
Put on baking sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: 8-minute strawberry cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth and then gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping and blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with lots of sliced, fresh strawberries to cover top. Add dollops of whipped topping on top, if desired.

title: queen o'cakes
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, vanilla, honey and sugar.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour into 2 wax paper-lined pans.
Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 4 patties.
Fry in hot shortening in skillet.
Brown on both sides.

title: microwave munching cashew brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass bowl, put sugar and corn syrup.
Cook on High for 5 minutes, then add cashews and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Next, add butter and vanilla.
Cook on High for another 2 minutes.
Add soda and quickly stir.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight containers.

title: kraut
directions: To each quart of shredded cabbage, add 1 tablespoon pickling or coarse salt, 2 tablespoons vinegar and 1 tablespoon sugar. Fill jars with shredded cabbage.
Fill with hot water.
Put on cap loosely.
This will ferment in about 1 week.
When fermentation ceases, clean sealing edge of jar.
Screw band tight and process in boiling bath for 25 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar into crumbs.
Keep 1 1/2 cups for top of cake.
Mix water, molasses and soda and put into remaining crumbs.
Mix until real wet.
Pour in pan; spread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, combine the eggs, sugar and butter.
Add salt, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon; mix well.
Add to the zucchini mixture and mix.
Add nuts and mix again.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9-inch pie pan with vegetable spray.
Place all ingredients in blender, food processor or mixing bowl.
Blend 1 minute or beat 2 minutes with mixer. Pour into pie pan and bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.
To serve, cut pie into eight pieces.
One serving (1 piece) = 1 starch/bread exchange, 1/2 medium fat meat exchange. Contains 114 calories.

title: good meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Place in baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown and drain first 3 ingredients.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, Velveeta cheese and garlic salt.
Simmer until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Spread on rye bread.
Bake until bread is toasted.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Make small pan cornbread. Mix cornbread, margarine, 2 cups stuffing mix and 1/2 soup can of broth. Sprinkle some sage. In separate mixing bowl, mix 2 cans soup, rest of broth and sour cream. In casserole dish, layer chicken, soup mixture and cornbread mixture. Then layer again. Bake at 350°, covered, for 25 minutes, then uncovered 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together until crumbly.
Press half into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put remaining ingredients in saucepan; cook until clear and thick.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: garden vegetable medley
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet or Dutch oven over medium heat until hot. Add squash and onion. Cook and stir 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Add tomato slices and oregano. Cook and stir for 1 minute. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add taco sauce and cook and stir for 30 seconds. Reduce heat to low. Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook for 2 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: fruity salad
directions: Drain all fruit. Reserve juice. Mix 3 cups juice with pudding mix.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Remove from heat and cool.
Once cooled, mix with fruit and chill to serve.

title: potato-broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven over low heat; add flour, cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add cream cheese, cut in cubes, Swiss cheese, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Add potatoes and stir well.
Spoon one half of potato mixture into a lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Spoon broccoli evenly over potatoes. Spoon remaining potatoes over broccoli layer.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to boil and add salt.
Add macaroni and cook about 10 to 12 minutes. Drain, saving 1 cup of the water.
In bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Add macaroni and mix well.
(May need to add saved water so dish won't be too dry.)

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add seasoning and refried beans. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and green taco sauce together.
Spread over meat mixture.

title: yule log pecan roll
directions: Melt chips over hot water (not boiling) and stir in milk and vanilla.
Add chopped nuts and mix well.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Form into 12-inch roll on waxed paper.
Unroll and mark with tines of fork lengthwise.
Brush with egg white.
Press pecan halves into roll to completely cover surface.
Wrap in waxed paper. Chill.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices with sharp knife.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 4 to 6-quart freezer.
Mix until freezer turns hard.
May add fresh or frozen fruit as desired.
May omit vanilla pudding and add chocolate pudding and add 1/4 cup cocoa.

title: pasta with plum tomatoes and asparagus
directions: Blanch asparagus.
Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes and wine.
Saute 5 minutes on low heat.
Add red pepper and salt.
Boil water and cook pasta.
When finished, toss in bowl.
Add tomato and asparagus and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and add other ingredients.
Make into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate to make firm.

title: apple cobbler
directions: In a 7 x 11-inch pan, fill less than 1/4 full of boiling water and add butter.
Add sugar, cinnamon and vinegar.
Set aside.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, milk and oil.
Add the can of frosting to batter (1/2 at a time).
Grease tube or bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Pour batter on top of nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.

title: dill deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in half.
Remove yolks; mash.
Combine with mayonnaise, pickle, cheese and salt.
Refill whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 12 halves.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients (except poppy seed).
Beat on medium for 3 minutes.
Add poppy seed and blend.
Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Glaze if you like with 3/4 cup powdered sugar, lemon juice and enough milk to spoon on the cake.

title: hungarian chicken
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion in melted Crisco until soft but not brown.
Stir in salt, paprika and pepper, then brown the chicken pieces on all sides.
Add chicken stock or bouillon. Cover and simmer for 50 to 60 minutes, until chicken is tender. Put chicken on a serving platter and keep hot.
Stir combined sour cream and flour into mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir until this sauce comes to a boil; pour over chicken.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: frosting mix
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 cup coconut and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour over cake while still warm.

title: martha's fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with a variety of fruits.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place crescent rolls onto ungreased pizza pan to make crust; trim edges.
Scramble eggs with salt and pepper.
Bake crust for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain eggs well.
Place onto baked crust.
Top with a layer of scrambled bacon pieces, scrambled sausage, any of the optional toppings and cheese.
Place in warm oven to melt cheese.
Serve warm.
Makes a great meal any time of day served with fresh fruit.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in double boiler or saucepan.
Add flour and seasoning; stir smooth.
Slowly add the milk, stirring constantly. When it thickens, melt the grated cheese in the sauce.
Put in a buttered baking dish or casserole with layers of the sliced potatoes, onion and cheese sauce, repeating until all ingredients are used.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop stalks of celery.
Chop onion. Mix together in a bowl along with turkey.
Roll into patties. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: party swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper the meat.
You can flour the meat, but I leave the flour off.
Brown in hot shortening or oil.
Pour off excess grease.

title: good brittle
directions: In a large pot, put the sugar, water, syrup and peanuts.
Cook until the peanuts pop and the sugar turns caramel in color.
Take off fire and add margarine, soda and vanilla.
Mix well; pour into pan to cool.
Break in pieces.

title: gulllivers creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except last two in a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter with flour, add to the corn, mix well and remove from heat.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with bread crumbs or cheese Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "old hearty" cottage supper
directions: Saute onion.
Add ground beef and cook, stirring, until brown. Add other ingredients and simmer, covered, at the back of wood stove or in a 325° oven until flavors have mingled and swimmers are dry.
May be doubled or tripled.

title: baked custard(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix liquids and sugar together; put in bottom of percolator. Put spices in top; perk for 3 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken breasts and artichoke hearts
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter/oleo.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in brandy, lemon juice, water and chicken bouillon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Using a wire whisk, gradually blend in sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover tightly; bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; add artichoke hearts.
Cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: veg-beef casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, alternate layers of raw beef, cabbage, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Dilute tomato soup with water and pour over casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: popeye's spinach
directions: Drain the spinach in a sieve; do not press out water.
Combine the spinach, soup mix, sour cream and bread crumbs; mix well. Blend in the eggs.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar; stir. Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after adding each egg.
Add flour and beat thoroughly. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Bake for 25 minutes
Cut in squares.

title: pecan chip  cake
directions: In a large bowl combine first five ingredients. Beat at 2 minutes or until well blended. Pour half of the batter into greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Combine pecans and chocolate chips. Sprinkle half over the batter. Top with marshmallows and remaining batter. Sprinkle with remaining pecan mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan. Immediately flip cake over on a serving plate. Serves 12 to 16.

title: german pancakes
directions: Beat eggs slightly in blender, then add other ingredients. Mix.
Beat at high for additional five minutes.
Put 1/2 to 3/4 cup mixture in large iron (or other oven-safe) skillet and cook on stove top until no longer runny (medium heat).
Place skillet in 450° oven until done (about one minute).
Serve with lemon juice and powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: country style steak and gravy
directions: Sprinkle
steak with tenderizer, Accent, salt and pepper on both
sides.
Flour steak well on both sides.
Fry steak in shortening	on
medium
to	high heat until brown on both sides approximately
minutes
on both sides each.
Remove from pan and
add
flour,
salt and pepper to fat in pan.
Brown lightly stirring.
Add
a
little
extra
shortening if necessary.	Add water and Worcestershire stirring until of a good gravy consistency.
Add
a little extra water if necessary.
You may return steak
to
gravy
and
simmer for 20 minutes covered or you may serve separately.

title: baked ziti with ricotta and sausage
directions: In a medium saucepan,
melt 4 tablespoons of butter and add the flour.	Stir and blend with a wire whisk and cook over medium heat for about
minutes.
Slowly
add
the
scalded chicken stock and wine
and keep whisking.	Allow the sauce to simmer for about 15
minutes.	Set
aside.
In
a medium bowl, combine the Ricotta with
half	the
Asiago cheese, beaten egg and 1 tablespoon parsley;
add
salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and set aside.	In
a
medium
skillet,
heat the oil and saute the sausage over
medium-high
heat for a few minutes or until done; set aside.

title: pepper steak(chinese)
directions: In
a
large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef and cook over high heat, stirring frequently until browned, about 5 minutes. Add pepper,
onion and celery.	Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Reduce
heat;	stir in molasses, soy sauce, lemon juice,
pepper
sauce
and	seasonings.
Blend water and cornstarch;
quickly
stir	into
beef
mixture.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with hot fluffy rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine first eight ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours. (Time will vary depending on baking dish.)

title: crab dip(quick and easy, but needs to be made the night before.)
directions: Mix together first four ingredients. Fill the bottom of a pie plate or fluted dish with this mixture. Spread cocktail sauce on top. Cover the layer of cocktail sauce with flaked crab meat or seafood chunks. Garnish with parsley. Allow to refrigerate overnight for best flavor!

title: hobo dinner
directions: Shape meat into patties; place on aluminum foil.
Top with potatoes, onion and carrots.
Wrap tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Butter and season patties and vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: In a large skillet, combine carrots, butter and caraway seed. Cook over low heat until the carrots are just crisp and tender, about 5 minutes.
Add soup, milk, water, cabbage and sausage; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook until cabbage is tender, about 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings (2 quarts).

title: spice tea
directions: Put all ingredients in a large container; mix thoroughly.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: Boil macaroni, add veggies for last 5 minutes of cooking. Drain.
In sauce pan, stir soup into cream cheese; add milk, parmesan cheese and pepper, over low heat.
Heat until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in macaroni and veggies.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Serves six.

title: rice and carrot mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in water.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Stir into gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Add mayonnaise and beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Fold in pineapple, rice, carrots and nuts.
Pour into 4 1/2 cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spray square casserole dish with cooking spray.
Cover bottom of pan with a layer of asparagus, then cheese and repeat until pan is filled.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients with shortening, using hands to work into crumbs.
Line a 9 inch pie plate with pastry, fill with liquid and top with crumbs.
Reserve small amount of crumbs for top.

title: light and easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add food coloring. Pour in graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together in food processor.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut into pieces and freeze overnight.
Cook under broiler until brown and bubbly.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Butter the French bread with 3 tablespoons of butter (cut bread lengthwise).
Spread mixture on 1/2 bread.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: lime gelatin, pineapple, cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix gelatin, using 2 cups boiling water, 1 1/3 cups cold water and 2/3 cup pineapple juice.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Make Dream Whip topping according to package directions.
Add chopped nuts, cottage cheese and salad dressing; mix well.
Whip gelatin after it reaches appropriate consistency with electric mixer until broken up into pea size pieces.
Add pineapple, minus 3 tablespoons, to whipped gelatin and stir together.
Add whipped mixture and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart Pyrex oblong glass dish sprayed with vegetable oil (like Pam). (Will also need another small dish as recipe makes a little more than fits in 2-quart dish.)
Can top with sliced olives or pineapple pieces, if desired.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 10-inch spring-form pan.
For crust, mix cracker crumbs with melted butter and press into pan. In large mixer bowl, blend sugar and eggs until light and thick. Gradually add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in melted chocolate, Kahlua and cocoa.
Mix in sour cream.
Fold in melted butter, then add mini chocolate chips; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours; let cool, then refrigerate.
Remove outer rim of pan to serve.
Baking time can vary depending on oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Keep warm. Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well (use hands).
Roll into balls and dip in chocolate mixture.
Lay on wax paper to cool.
Freezes well!

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until set in center.

title: vegi hot dish
directions: Mix soup, milk, California blend and seasoning salts.
Top with French fried onions, shredded cheese and Tater Tots in that order.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until vegies are tender.

title: pineapple monte cristo
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Brush margarine on both sides of each slice.
Top four slices ham and second slice of bread.
Arrange pineapple and cheese slices on top of each; cover with third slice of bread.
Secure with toothpicks; cut in half diagonally. Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Dip each half of sandwich in egg mixture.
Brown on all sides in skillet, adding more margarine, if needed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs together.
Pour on graham cracker crust.
Top with sliced bananas, pineapple and cherries.
Put Cool Whip on top and nuts on top of that.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine melted butter, 1 egg and cake mix.
Spread mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mashed potato pancakes
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Mash with enough milk to form a paste. Saute as an ordinary pancake.

title: apricot cheese salad
directions: Drain apricots and pineapple, separately.
Reserve 1 cup apricot syrup and 1 cup pineapple syrup.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Stir in reserved apricot syrup; chill until partially thickened.
Stir in apricots, pineapple and marshmallows. Chill until firm.
Combine sugar, flour, egg and butter; stir in reserved pineapple syrup; cook over low heat until thickened. Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over Jell-O mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: toots e. rolls
directions: Will also need a 1 gallon size Ziploc bag.

title: low-fat baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in Ranch dressing.
Roll them in bread crumbs and place on deep cookie sheet or broiler pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered, or until chicken is done.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut sausage in chunks or remove from casings and crumble. Brown meats in as little oil as possible.
Add onion and fresh garlic with green pepper and saute until tender.
Add all tomato products and the mushrooms.
If fresh mushrooms are used, saute with onions.
Add sugar and white wine.
Season with herbs to taste.
Simmer for several hours over very low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over pasta and top with grated cheese.

title: zucchini pie casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Butter a 3-quart casserole.
Layer as follows:
rice, chicken, cheese, zucchini and tomato.
Mix sour cream, chilies, oregano, garlic salt, green pepper and green onion.
(Salt and pepper, if desired.)
Pour over layered casserole.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated cheese and parsley.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german fried chicken
directions: Cover each piece with egg mixture and dip in plain bread crumbs.
Place chicken in frypan with 1/2-inch of hot vegetable oil.
If any egg mixture is left, pour over chicken pieces in pan. Fry chicken until done.

title: skor cake
directions: Make cake as directed on back of box.
When cool, poke holes in cake.
Mix together the milk, caramel topping and Cool Whip; spread on cake.
Top with Skor candy pieces.

title: turkey and dressing bake
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, mix celery, stuffing and mushrooms. Layer turkey evenly over stuffing.
Combine and mix well the milk, eggs and soup.
Pour over turkey.
Sprinkle with almonds; sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cashew cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Stir in cashews. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In a bowl, add foamy eggs and sugars. Beat in butter. Stir in morsels and nuts. Spoon into pie shell. Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all cheeses with mixer until blended.
Add salts. Blend and put on decorative dish with crackers and/or fresh vegetables.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Bake cake as usual; cool.
Poke holes in cake with a fork. Make jello as usual; pour over cake.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except slaw. Add slaw to mixture and stir. Refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt together.
Combine corn oil margarine and first amount of sugar.
Add egg whites.
Add lemon juice and lemon peel.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well. Chill dough for several hours.
Shape into balls.
Dip balls into second amount of sugar.
Place sugar side up on baking sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops. Spread mustard on each side. Roll in flour. Brown in oil. Place in casserole. Pour over mushroom soup. Bake until tender; a little water can be added.

title: marshmallow doughnuts
directions: Deep dry biscuits until golden brown.
Drain and cool.
Slice and fill with marshmallow cream.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until tender and drain.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Saute
onions
in
bacon	grease.
Blend	soup, sour cream,
beans
and	bacon.	Pour
in casserole, top with bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt) alternately with milk and vanilla. Divide batter into 2 portions. Into one part, put the cinnamon, allspice and cloves. Add the seeded, chopped raisins. Pour the batter into 4 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans. Make 2 spice layers and 2 light layers. Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until done. Cool layers and put together with filling, alternating light and dark layers. Frost top and sides of cake with a 7-minute icing.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions together until potatoes are tender. Drain and add to white sauce.
Heat together.

title: honey-yogurt dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together all the ingredients until well mixed.
Store in a tightly covered jar in the refrigerator and shake well before each use.
Use for fruit salads.
Makes 1 cup.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a lightly greased dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and milk; stir well.
Spoon sauce over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs; cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Swiss cheese slices can be omitted if desired.

title: cream cheese surprise
directions: Spray 10 x 13 x 2-inch cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread one can of crescent rolls in pan.
Stretch dough so it fills pan.
Seal seams.
Mix remaining ingredients except egg white and remaining crescent rolls.
Spread mixture over crescent rolls.
Spread remaining crescent rolls on wax paper.
Stretch to measure same size as pan.
Lay over top of cheese mixture. (Remove wax paper.)
Seal seams and edges.
Brush top with egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: punch bowl cake
