directions: Bake cake in two round cake pans as per directions.
Cook pudding and cool completely.
Cool cake, then slice strawberries. Layer as follows in punch bowl:
Cake, pudding, pineapple, a thin layer Cool Whip, then start again, cake, pudding, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Cook the stewing hen. Remove from bone, and cut up fine with kitchen shears. Place chicken in pot, and add broth. Bring to a boil. Add bread. Stir until bread dissolves into broth. Turn heat to low, and slowly stir in the well-beaten eggs. Cook until thickened. Serve on hot sandwich buns.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts; divide into 2 equal portions.
Shape into balls.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Let chill 12 hours before serving.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Mix egg and Cool Whip.
Add cake mix.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned corn relish
directions: Prepare first 7 ingredients.
Cook 1/2 hour; color with turmeric, and salt to taste.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Rub together flour, brown sugar, salt, spice and butter to make crumbs.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Cool and stir in molasses and beaten egg yolk.
Sprinkle half the crumbs on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour in molasses mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fruit jam
directions: Boil fruit and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes (by clock).
Remove from heat and quickly add any flavor Jell-O.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set.
This recipe is a very old recipe given to me by my first mother-in-law.
A bit of history, but a good pie.

title: four layer delight
directions: Put aside a small amount of nuts to garnish top.
Mix flour, nuts and margarine; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Mix 1/2 of Cool Whip with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
A teaspoon of vanilla may be added, if desired.
Spread over cooled crust.
Prepare pudding with milk and pour over second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and garnish with remaining nuts.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: *Have ready-yeast which has been dissolved in 1 cup warm water. Heat shortening, sugar, salt and water to melt shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir in flour and knead well.
Let raise, mix down once.
Roll to scant 1/2-inch thick. Spread with melted butter and cinnamon sugar mixture to taste. Roll up and cut 1/2-inch thick.
Let raise.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken then pick off or cube.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream with chicken.
Put in a 13 by 9 inch baking dish.
Add bread crumbs or Ritz crackers crumbs on top.
Put butter over the crumbs and chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: bon bons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, then shape into balls. Put in refrigerator 15 to 20 minutes. Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip candy balls in chocolate and paraffin mix with toothpicks. Let cool.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini and chicken broth until done. Put in blender with seasonings. Blend well. This can be frozen or served at once. When ready to serve, add milk, butter and salt to taste. This is especially good and is a good way to use zucchini.

title: reese's quick fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Press into a nonstick pan.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: sunshine cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl. Beat well. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir just until flour is moistened. Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fish stew
directions: Fry fat back to obtain drippings.
Cook onion until soft in hot grease.
Mix water, ketchup, sugar and pepper in a sauce pan. Add onion and bring mixture to a boil for about 10 minutes.
Add fish and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: apricot slush
directions: Boil water; add sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mix in lemonade and orange juice concentrate.
Cool.
Add apricot brandy. Freeze overnight (1 1/2 days is best).
Pour 7-up over top, let drain down sides, and pour another 7-Up on top again.
Enjoy.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in dates and walnuts.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes. While warm, cut in bars.
Cool.
Remove from pan. Roll in sifted powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix Ricotta and drained spinach.
Stuff uncooked manicotti shells and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: hidden valley ranch red pepper dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Best if chilled overnight.
Garnish with chives.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: sheila's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and powdered sugar.
Cream in the eggs and vanilla.
Mix in the dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: manicotti(low-fat)
directions: Mix all of the cheeses, parsley, salt, pepper and seasonings in a bowl.
Take this mixture and put in uncooked manicotti with a teaspoon until tube is full.
Lay filled manicotti in baking dish and pour tomato sauce over the top.
Add water to come just to the top of the manicotti.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham-potato chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add potatoes, water, and seasonings. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Make a paste of the flour and 1/2 c. water; add to potato mixture.
Add milk and cook until slightly thickened.
Stir in undrained corn and ham.
Heat through.
(This soup tastes even better the day after you make it!)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut up shrimp.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls (2) or put into serving dish.
Serve with crackers.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: rose's brunch for a bunch
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt. Layer sausage, cheese and green pepper over top.
Combine eggs and milk in bowl; mix well.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Put cocoa in medium saucepan.
Add sugar and flour; mix well dry before heating.
Then add very warm water and stir.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add milk and heat on medium-high.
Stir contents constantly with spatula to keep from burning.
When desired thickness is reached, add butter.
Serve over hot, buttered biscuits.

title: low-fat stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Drain; place in bowl of cold water to prevent sticking.
Set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese, egg, egg white, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Drain shells; pat dry.
Fill with cheese mixture. Spread approximately 1/2 cup sauce over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange shells over sauce and cover with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cover loosely with foil and bake 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: *You can substitute banana peppers instead of chilies, but you will have to saute them with your onions until soft.

title: cinnamon loafs
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients on high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour half of batter evenly in two loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
In small bowl, sir together sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half of mixture over batter. Pour remaining batter in pans and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Gently swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tests done.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in jar.
Use 2 1/2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in saucepan, stirring continuously until smooth and thick.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Cover with frosting made from the 4 egg whites.
Beat until they stand in peaks
by adding pinch of salt.
Then add 8 tablespoons granulated sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Spread over pies.
Preheat oven to 425° and brown pies lightly.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Melt caramels and pet milk in microwave. Stir in marshmallow cream. Serve with sliced fruit.

title: arroz con leche rice pudding
directions: Boil rice, water, salt hard for 5 minutes.
Drain excess water; add remaining ingredients.
Let milk come to a boil slowly. Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and cook until liquid is absorbed, approximately 20 minutes.
Taste for sweetness, and add more sugar to taste. Remove cinnamon stick and chill thoroughly before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together; beat eggs and add to mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and blend well.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time and beat well after each time.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts. Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork (dip in cold water ever so often) in one direction and then at right angles to form a cross.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: punch
directions: Bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes. Keep warm to serve. Leftover can be refrigerated for later use.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook sliced potatoes for 5 to 7 minutes until slightly crisp. Melt butter with onions. Combine sour cream, water, beaten eggs, salt and pepper. Put potatoes in well-greased 1-quart casserole dish. Slowly pour over sauce mixture over the potatoes. Top with cheese and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pistachio wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at high speed until smooth.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour in batter; bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: green rice
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rocky road clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips over warm water.
Stir until smooth; add rest of ingredients and, when well coated, drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Yields 3 dozen medium size pieces.

title: oven pork steak
directions: Brown pork steaks in large skillet, then remove pork to roasting pan.
Make gravy with flour, water, salt and pepper in skillet with meat drippings.
Add 1 teaspoon of instant coffee to gravy or enough to give gravy a nice brown color.
Place sliced potatoes and onion on top of meat; pour gravy over all.
Cover the roasting pan; bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: peach cream pecan meringue
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Form pie shell.
Bake 55 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook chicken until done and tender.
Take meat from bones and place in greased baking dish.
Set aside.
Bring chicken broth and soup to a boil.
Add margarine and buttermilk; bring to a boil. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Do not stir! Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 450°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook meat in small amount of oil.
Pour into large bowl and use same saucepan for sauce.

title: butter dips
directions: Melt butter in bowl.
Mix flour, milk, sugar, baking powder and salt to a soft dough in bowl with fork.
Gently smooth the dough into a bowl on a cloth covered board; knead 10 times.
Roll dough into an 8-inch square.
Cut into strips.
Dip each in margarine.
Place on pan; bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add
egg
at
a time and beat well after each egg.
Sift
all
dry ingredients together.
Put sour cream in small bowl.
Add all flavoring to sour
cream
and mix well with
spoon.
Alternately
mix
sour cream mixture and dry ingredients into butter mixture.
(Start with flour and end with sour cream.) Grease and flour tube pan and bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Excellent!!

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture until it looks like rice grains.
Add milk to flour mixture gradually.
Stir with fork until it forms soft dough; knead.
Roll to 1/4-inch.
Spread with melted butter. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll into pinwheels; cut into 12 biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen biscuits.

title: diabetic pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add the spice mixture to the pumpkin mix.
Beat well, then pour into serving dessert dishes.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Very good.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over meat, coating well. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Better if it stays in marinade longer.
Great for chicken to grill.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onions; cook according to pkg. directions. Drain and add remaining ingredients; stir well. Pour into greased 2-quart shallow casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serves 6-8.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla and stir well. Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of 8 or 9-inch round cake pan with wax paper.
Spray with Pam also.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Watch closely the last 5 minutes as it tends to brown quickly.)
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out and cool completely.
Cut in half and put both cut sides up with strawberries (smash strawberries up and add a little sugar) in middle and on top.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir about 8 minutes or until thick and creamy.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Can be done in the microwave or in a pan.
In a quart glass, cook sugar, cream, corn syrup and 4 squares of chocolate on High for 4 minutes.

title: lasagne(serves 8)
directions: Brown beef in oil and garlic. Add onion. Add next 6 ingredients. Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes. Cook noodles 15 to 20 minutes. Rinse and drain. In rectangular 1 1/2-quart pan, put layers of noodles, Mozzarella, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan. Repeat. Bake at 350° until done or bubbly.

title: plaza soup
directions: Make a roux from butter and flour.
Slowly add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Place chicken in a large baking dish in single layer.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: homemade banana bread(easy to make)
directions: Blend in mixer the sugar, egg, salt, margarine and vanilla. Add the bananas, baking soda, flour and raisins and nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased and floured loaf pan. Double the recipe and freeze one loaf.

title: bean burritos
directions: Mash beans and cook on medium heat in a nonstick skillet.
Add onion, sauce and cheese.
Spoon into burritos and place in casserole dish.

title: fred navey's favorite pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 4 deep crust pies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: mexican manicotti(microwave)
directions: Combine ground beef, refried beans, oregano and cumin.
Mix well. Fill uncooked manicotti shells with meat mixture.

Arrange in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Combine water and picante or taco sauce; pour over shells. Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 10 minutes, giving dish a half turn once. Using tongs, turn shells over.
Microwave, covered, on Medium for 17 to 19 minutes or until pasta is tender, giving dish a half turn once.
Combine sour cream, green onion and olives.
Spoon down center of casserole. Top with cheese. Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ma's quick doughnuts
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in large bowl. In medium bowl, combine eggs (well beaten) with sugar and milk.
Stir well.
Mix this with dry ingredients.
Stir well. Handle dough very little.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut and fry in hot shortening until brown.
Turn over, brown other side. Remove and lay on paper towel to drain.

title: alcohol window cleaner
directions: Measure water and detergent into a clean spray bottle large enough to permit shaking the contents.
Add alcohol.
Close top and shake to blend.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred green pepper, cabbage, onion and carrot together in a bowl; sprinkle sugar over all.
Boil vinegar, oil, salt, celery salt and dry mustard; pour over vegetables.
This salad keeps for days and is for a crowd.

title: pittsburg potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: amish pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening; add water and mix.
Roll in shape on floured board.

title: little smokies
directions: Thoroughly cook the Smokies in bacon grease.
Heat the jelly and sauce together in a saucepan.
Place Little Smokies in a chafing dish; cover with the sauce.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Drain and mash.
Add oleo and sugar. Place half of mixture in a casserole dish.
Layer rest of ingredients.
Add 1/2 of grated cheese.
Add 1/2 can of soup.
Add 1/2 of crackers.
Repeat layers.
Crackers will be on top.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Saute chopped onion in 1 tablespoon butter for 6 minutes.
Mix potatoes, onion, cheese, egg, salt, pepper and parsley with mixer on low speed until smooth; make patties (about 1/3 cup each).
Dip patties in flour and saute in butter over medium heat (about 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown).
Delicious with sour cream or buttermilk dressing on it.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all and chill.
Will get stronger after sits in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.
Can serve 20 people.

title: tuna parfaith
directions: Mix together and serve on lite bread or low-fat crackers.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Brown onion in a little butter or margarine.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat until all dissolved.
Slit 1 pound of hot dogs longways until open not all the way.
Spoon sauce over hot dogs.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve in hot dog rolls.

title: pork and vegetable soup
directions: Cut pork in 1/2-inch cubes.
Shake with flour in a plastic bag until coated.
Heat oil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add pork and brown slightly.
Add onion.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add celery, bouillon cubes, water and marjoram.
Bring to boiling, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add crushed soda crackers and milk.
Mix together and sprinkle on top of tomato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chuck's fancy pintos
directions: Saut a small slice of country ham in a heavy cooking pot until the fat is rendered.
Then saut chopped onion in the ham fat. Add a mixture of water and canned or fresh vegetable stock to the pot, and then add the dried pinto beans.
Fresh or new crop pintos are best. The liquid should just cover the beans. Bring to a boil and immediately reduce the heat to a low simmer.
Add water or stock as needed.
Keep a close eye on the beans so they are always covered with a little liquid.
Cooking time depends on the freshness of the beans.
Stop cooking before the beans get too mushy.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper. Line the bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with cabbage. Spread rice on cabbage.
Add meat and onion mixture.
Pour soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: almond rusks
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Blend in almond extract.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream and almonds.
Divide dough into 6 parts.
Shape into 15-inch long rolls.
Place 3 rolls on each of two ungreased cookie sheets. Allow space between, as they spread in baking.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove rolls from pans and cut diagonally into 3/4-inch slices.
Place slices, cut side down, on cookie sheet.
Return to oven.
Toast 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Turn Rusks and do the other side.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: poor man's cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and flour together.
Spread butter on foil in pan.
Pour in batter and place undrained peaches on top. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (start timing after a full boil is reached).
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and nuts.
Beat until blended. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Coconut or dates may be added if desired.

title: california garden pizza(summer pizza)
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, Hidden Valley dressing and lemon or lime juice together and refrigerate for at least 2 hours so flavors can blend.

title: irresistable brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter on stove.
Remove.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix with spoon until well blended.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and place onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat sugar and milk into cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in coconut and then Cool Whip.
Spoon into a graham cracker crust. Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: fresh vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring to a boil all ingredients except spinach and pepper.

Reduce heat. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are tender. Add spinach. Cook 2 minutes. Season with pepper. A small amount of olive oil can be added at the beginning along with a chopped tomato, if desired. Serves 8.

title: katie's mac and cheese
directions: In Dutch oven, add 6 cups water.
Add salt and bring to a boil. Add macaroni, stirring occasionally.
When macaroni is tender, pour into colander, drain thoroughly and return to pan.
On low heat, add milk, margarine and cubed Velveeta.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.

title: choco-cheese and chip muffins
directions: Make chocolate cake batter according to box directions; set aside.
Cream together sugar and softened cream cheese.
Add egg. Stir in chocolate chips.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 2-quart casserole. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef taco salad
directions: In medium skillet, fry ground beef and onion; drain off fat. Add taco seasoning and mix well.

title: my grandmother's rolls
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, salt and hot water.
Let stand until shortening melts.
Add egg.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water and add to first mixture.
Add flour and let rise until double in bulk.
Work down and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Let rise again.
Bake at 325°.

title: italian rice
directions: Boil water as directed.
Add chicken cubes.
Add rice, tomatoes, garlic, spinach and onion.
When water boils again, simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste.

title: harwood's enchilada soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Add all ingredients, except cheese. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add cheese and simmer another 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and salt until tender.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Fry meat until it is no longer pink.
Add chopped onion near the last and cook until they are tender.
Mix ingredients with tomato soup.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini and meat casserole
directions: Crumble and brown ground meat.
Drain well and place in mixing bowl.
In a small amount of oil brown onion rings and pepper rings.
Drain well and mix with meat.
Remove pulp and seeds from zucchini and chop or slice.
Place in a small amount of oil and saute until just fork-tender.
Drain dry.
Add to other ingredients.
Add spaghetti sauce to moisten.
Also add salt, pepper, garlic powder, oregano and sweet basil to taste.
Place in baking dish over rice or pasta.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated 4 bean salad
directions: Combine
sugar,
vinegar,
oil,
salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and onion.
Toss several times while chilling. Best
if served after refrigerating overnight.
Can be kept in refrigerator at least a week.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and cook until tender. Put in a casserole dish.
Add cheese, mayonnaise and margarine. Mix all together.
Put crumbled up crackers on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This casserole dish freezes well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Beat with mixer until creamy.
Add other ingredients and beat well. Put in buttered casserole dish. Add topping.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: cheese burgers
directions: You grill the meat with the cheese on it for 10 minutes.
You let it cool off a little.
Put the hamburgers buns on the meat and cheese and then eat them.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, and carrots, set aside.
Mix together mushroom soup and sour cream, set aside.
Mix together dressing mix and margarine.
Put a thin layer of dressing on the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Layer vegetables and sauce.
Top with the remaining dressing.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients; mix well.
Combine milks and heat to scalding point; add and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell(s).
Bake in 350° (moderate) oven 1 1/2 hours for deep 10-inch or about 1 hour for 9-inch pies.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix well and let set overnight. Put in container with lid to keep.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spread half mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.
Top with sour cream and then remaining jello mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese grit casserole
directions: Mix ingredients with grits that have been cooked in water for 5 minutes.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs 20 minutes before done. Serves 8.

title: aunt lisa's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Add broccoli, mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: miniature cheese cake
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners and put a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each.
In small bowl, beat all ingredients except pie filling until light and fluffy.
Fill liners 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Top each with spoonful of filling.

title: chunky pizza soup
directions: In saucepan heat oil; add onion, pepper and mushrooms. Stir-fry until soft, but not browned.
Add tomatoes, stock, basil and pepperoni; cook until heated through.
Mix 2 cheeses; ladle soup into 4 ovenproof bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Or microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve immediately with some warm crusty French bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add milk and cheese; heat until cheese melts. Cool.
Add beaten eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over macaroni.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 1 heaping teaspoonful to 1 cup boiling water.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart glass dish.
Mix beaten eggs, cornbread mix, black pepper, garlic salt, sugar and onion.
Fold in drained cottage cheese and broccoli.
Pour over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 24 to 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease bottom of pan with butter.
Mix milk, flour and sugar into mixing bowl.
Add peaches into mix and stir good.
Bake in 300° oven.
Cook until brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in bottom of buttered dish. Sprinkle with salt. Crumble rest of ingredients over apples and sprinkle with nuts. Bake 40 to 45
minutes in a 350° oven.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Put one stick oleo in skillet; saute the onion and bell pepper until tender.
Set aside.

title: swiss ham and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, cook onions in oleo until tender.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except French fried onions.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Uncover and top with French fried onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Boil sugar and syrup for a skimp minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter.
Add cornflakes; stir.
Drop on wax paper in clusters or roll in balls.

title: fruit filled spice bars
directions: Combine gingerbread mix, applesauce and water. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Fold in fruit. Spread on a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool. Frost with the white frosting prepared by package directions, substituting lemon juice for the water. Cut into bars.

title: apple caramel bars
directions: Crust:
Cream together the margarine and shortening; add the brown sugar and flour.
By hand, stir in oatmeal, salt and baking soda.
Reserve 2 cups of the mixture and pat the rest into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 5-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk and pour on butter.
Do not stir.
Add peaches on top of this.
Add remaining sugar over this.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in iron skillet.
Cook until the mixture boils.
Stir often.
Remove skillet from stove and add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Take a tablespoon of mixture and roll into ball.
Drop in coconut and roll.

title: peggy's old-fashioned syrup cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and syrup.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with the buttermilk.
Bake in a greased and floured 10 x 14 x 2-inch baking pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This is a good "all around" type cake.

title: old-fashioned ginger cookies
directions: Mix each ingredient thoroughly with next before adding another.
Refrigerate 4 hours to overnight.
Roll.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: hopping john
directions: Soak peas overnight. Drain.

title: grasso chicken
directions: In pan of 1/4 cup olive oil, saute fresh tomatoes, scallions and 1 clove fresh garlic.
Mix sour cream and eggs.
Dip boneless breasts in mixture, then flour.
Place in 1/4 cup olive oil on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove.
Add fresh tomato mixture.
Top with Asiago cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes. Remove.
Let set 10 minutes and eat.

title: mini ham puff(pampered chef recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chopped ham, mustard, pepper, beaten egg and onion in small bowl.
Unroll and then roll out crescent rolls.
Cut into 24 pieces.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Mix with all other ingredients well.
Line 8-inch pie pans with heavy foil extended at least 5 inches beyond rim.
Divide filling into each pan.
Fold foil over; seal and freeze.
Remove from pans.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Separate biscuits and place in pan, turning to completely cover.
Coat with margarine. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In plastic bag or bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until vegetables are coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan.
Discard bag.
Bake, stirring once, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 (1/4-cup) servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and chestnuts.
Mix with onions, celery, mayonnaise, pepper and mushroom soup.
Pour into casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until very light.
Measure and sift dry ingredients, add to egg mixture with mashed potatoes.
Mix only until well blended. Chill dough thoroughly before rolling out, an hour or two if possible.
Roll dough about 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat at 375° for about 3 minutes. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: "fix and mix" raisin bran muffins
directions: Beat together in large bowl with whisk the first 7 ingredients.
Whisk each ingredient as added.
Add Raisin Bran cereal.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full or use papers.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: french russian dressing
directions: Combine vinegar, chili sauce, minced onion, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and garlic.
Cover; let stand 1/2 hour. Gradually beat in Mazola oil.
Chill.
Remove garlic before serving.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Cover vegetables with water.
Bring to a boil.
Crumble and brown sausage.
Remove vegetables from heat when tender.
Do not overcook.
Add sausage, V-8 juice and spices.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove and discard the tops from tomatoes. Scoop out the tomato pulp.
Put it through a coarse sieve and mix it thoroughly with the tuna and 2 slices of bread trimmed of crust and crumbled with garlic powder and basil.
Divide the filling among the tomatoes.
Sprinkle the tomatoes with the dry bread crumbs and Parmesan mixed with the melted butter.
Arrange the stuffed tomatoes in an oiled baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until they are heated through and the topping is browned.

title: oven parmesan chips
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4 inch slices; place on a greased baking sheet in a single layer.
Mix butter, onion, salt, pepper and paprika.
Bush on one side of potatoes, then turn and brush other side.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or potatoes are tender and golden.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: multi-purpose sweet dough
directions: Insert dough
hooks
into
mixer.
In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in
warm
milk
and
add
sugar.
Let
rest
for 5 minutes. Add
margarine and eggs to yeast mixture and beat on speed 2. Turn
to speed 6 and add 1 cup flour and salt.
Turn to speed
2 and
gradually
add remaining flour.
(Total mixing/kneading time should be 6 to 8 minutes.) Remove dough from mixing bowl.
Form a ball and roll in greased bowl until dough ball is well-greased. Cover and let rise in a draft-free area for 1 1/2
hours.
Punch down
and
let
rise for 40 minutes. Punch down, remove from bowl and let rest on floured board for 10 minutes.

title: green chili-rice
directions: In large bowl, combine and mix all ingredients, adding a little salt if you like. Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, then remainder of ingredients. Place in unbaked pie shell and bake about 30 minutes in a slow oven (325°) or until slightly brown and the liquid sets.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange tomatoes and zucchini in rows in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine oil, parsley, shallots, garlic, basil, thyme, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake for 30 minutes, basting occasionally with the liquid in the pan.

title: spinach spread
directions: Make a shell of King's Hawaiian bread.
Put in freezer to make easier to slice.
Take out the center of the loaf.
Put dip in the hole.
Use the center piece of the bread to put dip on.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put in bowl, stir once or twice and set aside for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs in a large bowl with a mixer for 3 minutes, until light and fluffy.
Stir in bananas, flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Add sour cream and nuts.
Stir until well mixed. Pour batter into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Check by inserting a toothpick in the center.
When it comes out dry, cake is done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: sweet garlic with chicken pasta
directions: Cook and stir garlic in hot oil until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes and green onions.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add broth; simmer.
Add chicken and cooked noodles.
Heat through.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let pie cool and top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: shrimp-crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Put in a buttered casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Add oil and vanilla. Pour cold water over mixture and mix well "by hand."
Pour into an 8-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. When cool, frost, if desired.

title: cheese-stuffed meatballs
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion and salt.
Divide into 12 parts.
Shape meat firmly around each cheese cube to form meatballs.
Brown in skillet in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir now and then.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into patties.
Cook in skillet in hot oil; cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix the flour with all spices except orange peel.
Mix butter and sugar together gradually, then add egg, orange peel and molasses.
Gradually add flour and spice mixture.
Mixture is very thin.
Cover with Saran Wrap and towel and leave on counter in warm place overnight.
Will thicken.
Grease pan.
Take small amounts and roll very thin.
Cut in small shapes.
Bake at 300° about 8 to 10 minutes until brown.
Let cool and then put in airtight container.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix the butter, sugars and flour together like cornmeal; save 1 cup for the topping.
To remainder, add remaining ingredients.
Mix and put in two 8 x 12-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot herb bread
directions: Combine butter, herbs and seed.
Cut bread in half lengthwise. Spread each with butter.
Make crosswise cuts on the diagonal 2 inches apart.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat 4 minutes.
To serve, cut with scissors.

title: party beans
directions: Brown meat and drain, then add onion and celery. Cook until tender, then add tomato sauce and ketchup. Cook 20 minutes, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well, then bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half.
Scoop out the zucchini and leave the shell. Cook zucchini, oil, parsley and onion.
Let cool.
Brown ground beef and let cool.
Mix both with bread crumbs and eggs. Fill shells.
You can put a can of Italian stewed tomatoes over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Very good with a serving of rice.

title: dream cake
directions: Combine cake mix (use whatever flavor cake mix), Dream Whip, eggs and water in large bowl.
Blend until moistened.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° as directed on cake mix box for size of pans.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Boil noodles.
Brown meat and onion together in frypan.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add soup; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add sour cream; blend well, then fold in noodles.
This will hold on simmer for quite a while or can be reheated.
Serve as a casserole or on a platter.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lou's chicken salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, curry powder, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Add rice, chicken, celery, onions and peas; mix well. Chill for 2 hours minimum.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese, ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ham, cheese, broccoli and soup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir remaining ingredients until dough forms; drop by spoonful evenly over broccoli mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat egg; add to creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture, just until blended. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break
angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Place in a 9
x 12-inch
pan.
Cream the confectioners sugar and cream cheese. Add milk and Cool Whip;
mix well.
Pour mixture over cake. Refrigerate
hour.
Slice
strawberries and mix with glaze. Spoon over cake mixture.
Refrigerate.
Delicious!

title: wild rice
directions: Mix beef broth and enough water to make 2 cups. Add onions and boil. Add rinsed wild rice and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add long grain rice. Return to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 additional minutes. Toss with butter or bacon drippings and parsley. Add chopped pimiento and bacon crumbles.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray three 9-inch round cake pans with Pam.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks, whole eggs and sugar with an electric mixer for at least 5 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Stir margarine pieces into hot milk until it is melted. Combine flour with baking powder.
Add 1/2 cup flour mixture into egg mixture, beating slowly.
Add half the hot milk mixture, 1 cup flour mixture, then the remaining hot milk; beating after each addition.
Add remaining flour mixture and vanilla.
Beat well. Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes, remove from pans and cool completely.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn; pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soup and onion; pour over corn and beans.
Sprinkle cheese over it; crush crackers and sprinkle next.
Melt butter; drizzle over crackers.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and scrumptious frosting
directions: Boil butter, milk and sugar 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Beat until of spreading consistency. Perfect for brownies or 24 cupcakes.

title: sicilian potato salad
directions: Saute onion in a tablespoon of olive oil until golden.
Remove from pan; drain on paper towels.
Cut the potatoes into chunks; boil just until tender.
Drain and cool.
Core the peppers; cut into strips.
Saute in olive oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Cut the tomatoes into chunks.
Make dressing.

title: italian sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shell in hot oven at 450° for 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Saute zucchini in 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet until tender.
Remove to bowl.
Remove casing from sausage; crumble and cook in butter until no longer pink.
Drain on paper towel.
Spread zucchini evenly over pastry shell; sprinkle crumbled sausage and Swiss cheese over zucchini.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl; add milk, cream, Parmesan cheese, salt and white pepper.
Blend well.
Pour into pastry shell and bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake for 15 minutes more or until center is almost firm but still soft.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
If using a normal pie pan, you will have to divide into two pans.
Otherwise, use a deep square pan or dish.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt mary's antipasto
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil for one minute.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except sardines. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and marinate about a week.
Add sardines just before serving. Serve with assorted crackers if desired.

title: barbecue meatballs(appetizers)
directions: Simmer in crock-pot until meatballs are warm.

title: june glaze's hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a tightly covered container.
One serving equals 1/2 cup mix plus 1/2 cup boiling water.

title: fried or squaw bread
directions: Mix the ingredients together, adding more flour, if necessary, to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board until it is very thin.
Cut into strips, about 2 x 3-inches.
Drop in deep fat. Brown on one side.
Turn and brown on the other side.
Serve hot.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls into hot grease. Drain. Can be served as a side dish with any meat, plain, or served with syrup, butter or confectioners sugar.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all together and heat at 350° for 1 hour or microwave for 5 minutes.

title: maque choux
directions: Cut kernels of corn down cobs and cut off cobs.
Scrape milk off cobs also.
Chop tomatoes, onion and bell pepper; salt and pepper.
Spray large skillet with Pam.
Add ingredients.
Cook on medium fire with cover.
Stir every so often.
Serves 8.

title: jamaican jerked chicken
directions: Place soy sauce, lime juice, ginger, garlic, onions and peppers in food processor.
Puree until smooth.
Transfer to mixing bowl.
Stir in vinegar, brown sugar, Crisco, allspice, molasses, cinnamon, thyme, pepper, nutmeg and cloves.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Adjust seasonings with soy sauce, lime juice and brown sugar.
Marinade should be spicy, gingery, mildly hot and slightly sweet and sour.
Place 16 to 24 chicken thighs with skin removed in large resealable plastic bag.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Seal bag.
Refrigerate 2 days.
Turn occasionally. Grill or broil; turn frequently to avoid charring.

title: shrimp marinade
directions: Boil shrimp in shell, drain.
Put in marinade 24 hours, serve cold.
Peel your own.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini for 5 minutes.
Saute carrots and onion (use Pam).
Mix soup and sour cream.
Layer zucchini, soup and carrots, with croutons in each layer, in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually while beating constantly.
Fold in salt, vanilla and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter a 10 x 6 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch glass baking dish.
Toast bread lightly.
Butter while hot with margarine.
Cut slices in halves or quarters.
Fit neatly in prepared dish, overlapping slightly.
Sprinkle raisins between slices, not over top.
Scald milk.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break tops of flowers of broccoli into small bowl.
Slice onion; divide into rings and add to broccoli.
Crumble bacon and add raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over salad and toss.
Chill about 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: appetizers
directions: Fry bacon until very crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Combine crumbled bacon, chopped onion and mayonnaise; blend.
Spread a teaspoon of mixture on each round.
Bake at 350° for a few moments.

title: fresh and fruity
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend 1 minute or until smooth.
Makes 1 tall glass.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients together and blend well. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ham wellington with chutney
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Remove gelatin from ham; place ham in a greased, shallow baking pan.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat together butter, sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Mix with dry ingredients just until flour is mixed in.
Fold in cranberries and pecans.
Pour in greased muffin pan.
Before baking, sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, mixed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion; boil 10 to 12 minutes. Add seasonings and shredded cheese. Stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream and butter; stir and heat to boiling.
Slowly add water to flour, stirring constantly, until texture is smooth. Slowly add to hot mixture, stirring rapidly. Cook and stir until soup is the consistency of heavy cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli supreme casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in heavy kettle.
Drain and add onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Do not drain vegetables.
Simmer
for 15 minutes.
Top each serving with grated cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening until crumbly. Combine and add egg, water and vinegar.
Mix together by hand until mixture leaves sides of bowl.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Very easy to roll out and will keep up to 2 weeks. Makes 4 crusts.

title: margaret's baked beans
directions: Pour off some of the liquid from the beans.
Add green pepper, onion, brown sugar, corn syrup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place bacon on top.

title: fruit and cheese pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover 14-inch pizza pan with foil.
Cut cookie dough into 1/8 to 1/4 inch rounds.
Arrange in slightly overlapping pattern on prepared pan, covering pan completely. Press dough together to seal.
Bake until puffed and golden, about 10 minutes.
This may be made 8 hours ahead.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, pineapple, pecans and soda with wooden spoon.
Bake in loaf pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot turkey(easy!)
directions: Put seasoned turkey breast in crock-pot.
Do not add water. Cook on low all night or all day.
Delicious! (Makes great turkey salad.)

title: raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round pans.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.

title: play dough
directions: Boil salt and water together.
Add food coloring.
After salt dissolves, remove from heat and add salad oil, powdered alum and flour.
Mix thoroughly, then knead while still warm, until color is evenly distributed and lumps are gone.
Store in airtight container or plastic bag tightly closed.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Combine
eggs,	mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, onion and Tabasco.
Fold in crab meat.
Spoon into individual baking dishes or	casserole
dish.
Top with bread crumbs and butter mixed. Bake
in
350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: wassail
directions: Combine juices in saucepan. Tie spice in cheesecloth.
Add to juice.
Simmer 30 minutes. Remove spices and serve hot.

title: avocado soup
directions: Place half of chicken broth and the remaining ingredients in blender container.
Blend on medium speed until smooth.
Stir remaining broth into the avocado mixture.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with sour cream and paprika, if desired. Yields 6 servings.

title: sherried eggs and sausage
directions: Generously butter 4 sherried egg dishes. Break 2 eggs into each dish without puncturing the yolk.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, then sprinkle more generously with the seasoned salt. Grind pepper over the eggs.

Dribble 2 tablespoons of the cream over the egg yolks in each dish. Sprinkle generously with Romano. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 12 to 18 minutes, depending on firmness desired and the material from which your sherried egg dishes are made.
Arrange sausage around the eggs. Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, gradually adding sugar.
Beat on medium speed about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add 1 cup flour sifted with spices.
Mix dried apples with the soda added to them and sweetened with a small amount of sugar.
Stir in raisins (cut up, if preferred). Add pecans and pour in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: white grape apple butter
directions: Wash and quarter apples removing blossom end, no need to core or pare.
In a large kettle, cook apples in juice until soft, about 45 minutes.
Cool and press through a sieve or food mill. There should be 4 to 5 cups apple pulp.
Add sugar and spices. Cook slowly, stirring often to prevent sticking, for 1 hour or until thick.
Pack into sterilized jars, adjust lids and process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: gold bar candy
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and liquid flavoring.
Pour into a medium bowl.
Beat with electric mixer on high speed for 4 or 5 minutes or until thick and is no longer glossy.
Stir in pecans.
Fill buttered plastic ice cube trays half full with mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove and wrap in foil candy wrappers.
Store in a cool place.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add tomato soup and green beans. Top with mashed potatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked fruit
directions: Pour in baking dish put 2 Tbsp. butter on top and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Spread out each biscuit in cups of muffin pan (1 per cup). Spread dough to rim of cup.
Brown ground beef and drain off excess grease.
Add barbecue sauce to beef and simmer for 5 minutes.
Fill each dough cup with beef mixture.
Sprinkle each cup with cheese.
Bake according to directions on biscuit can. Makes 10 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy, add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla and mix lightly but well.
Combine and add dry ingredients, stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans 9 x 5 x 3 inch. in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: lynnette's applesauce cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce.
Stir in eggs.
Put all dry ingredients in a sifter.
Add to batter slowly.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.

title: california rangers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large bowl combine first 6 ingredients and set aside. Combine eggs, honey, molasses, oil, buttermilk and boiling water. Mix into bowl of dry ingredients and add mashed banana.
Spoon into greased or papered muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Batter may be made up ahead of time and stored in refrigerator for up to one month to be used as needed.
You can substitute Mueslix cereal for part of the bran.
Yields approximately 3 dozen muffins.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Combine crumbs, peanut butter and sugar; work until smooth. Press into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips over hot water (double boiler).
Spread over cracker mixture.
Cool until firm.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together.
Put on greased pizza pan.
Work the crust out to the edge of your pan with your fingers and make the crust thin. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss alpine pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Slightly cook broccoli; drain well and chop into 1/2-inch pieces.
Layer ham, cheese, broccoli and onions in pie crust, using two layers.
Add eggs (beaten) to scalded milk; add salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for additional 35 minutes.
Remove and let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add meat and brown. Transfer meat mixture and all remaining ingredients to rice cooker.
Press cook; jambalaya will be ready in 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cream
cheese. Mix in sour cream.
Add onion and clams. Add
dash	of
Tabasco and lemon juice, Worcestershire and paprika to taste.

title: date roll candy
directions: Cook sugar, salt and milk together to soft-ball stage.
Add package of dates and cook until mixture reaches firm ball.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until thickens.
Roll in a damp cloth (smooth-not terry).
Chill and slice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread crescent roll dough in baking pan, sealing perforations. Bake, using package directions, until lightly browned. Combine cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well. Spread over baked layer. Top with mixture of chopped vegetables.

title: simple stew
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chicken.
Add other ingredients, stirring to boil.
Simmer and cook 2 hours.
Stir frequently!!

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and oil.
Fold in eggs and add alternately the dry ingredients and milk.
Mix thoroughly and add nuts, cooked prunes and vanilla.
Bake in a regular sheet cake pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in a skillet and set aside.
Blend soup and milk well.
Add potatoes and mix.
Pour into a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Place chops on top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: kielbasa
directions: If fresh kielbasa is used, brown first whole.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Cook onions and garlic in bacon fat until soft. Put all ingredients in casserole or Dutch oven; kielbasa on bottom, then kraut, bacon, onions, tomatoes and beer.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in the oven.
Low simmer on the stove-top.

title: miss thompson's meat loaf
directions: Combine well the ground meats, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, ketchup, mustard, 2 eggs, thyme, salt and pepper to taste.
Spread the mixture out on a large piece of waxed paper or parchment paper into a rectangle, about 15 x 12-inches.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours. Preparation time is 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except liquid.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Cover with liquid and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes.

title: native american cranberry sauce
directions: Bring syrup, water and ginger to a boil in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in cranberries.
Simmer until berries begin to pop, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Turn into bowl and let cool.
Refrigerate.
(Can be prepared 3 days ahead.)
Makes about 4 cups.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla. With spoon, fold in pecans.
With spoon, drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and remove.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; take off bone.
Line bottom of baking dish with chicken.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken. Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Put on top of soup and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef pinwheel
directions: Lightly but thoroughly combine beef and bread crumbs, egg, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Combine spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan, Italian seasoning, remaining salt and garlic powder.
Place beef mixture on wax paper and pat into 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread spinach mixture over beef to 3/4 inch of edge on all sides.
Roll from small end.
Press beef over filling at ends.
Place loaf, seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour then spread catsup and bake 15 more minutes.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella on loaf.

title: salmon patties
directions: Chop pepper and onion.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Make into patties and fry until brown on both sides.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Makes a large batch, but very good.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Chop onion and slightly brown in margarine.
Slice potatoes in baking dish.
Pour onion and margarine mixture over potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and heat in oven until completely warmed and cheese is melted.

title: eclair cake
directions: Use 13 x 9 dish.

title: fiesta burritos
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil; heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Stir together taco mix, tomato juice and oil.
Brown beef in skillet.
Stir in beans and 1/2 cup of the tomato mixture.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes stirring occasionally until hot.
Place generous spoonful of this mixture on each tortilla.
Sprinkle with lettuce and cheese and roll up.
Place seam side down in greased shallow casserole dish. Pour remaining tomato mixture over burritos.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices. Combine soup and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle melted butter over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Beat until smooth in a large bow.
Pour batter into 2 cake pans (round) or one 9x13x2 cake pan.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Using either our sugar-free lemon pie or strawberry/raspberry pie filling, which are fat-free, also make a fat-free crust. First prepare the filling per either recipe, and at once wipe inside of a 9 or 10-inch pie pan or Pyrex pie plate with a few tablespoons hot filling.
Then quickly dust in finely crushed corn flakes, shaking out excess crumbs.
Refrigerate pie pan or plate about 10 minutes and then pour in completely cooled filling. Allow pie to stand until filling begins to thicken.
Transfer pie carefully to refrigerator.
Serve when quite firm, according to the recipes for either pie mentioned.

title: boeuf bourguignon
directions: In a skillet, brown beef cubes in oil.
Transfer to a Dutch oven.
Pour wine into skillet. Scrape up brown bits and pour over beef.
Add seasonings, tomato paste and broth to meat.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Transfer to oven.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Discard bay leaf.
Remove beef.
Make a roux of flour and 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and oil.
Add both to the Dutch oven along with beef and onions.
Mix well.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well!

title: cheese-stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti for 10 minutes; drain.
Cool in a single layer on waxed paper.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except sauce. Spoon into manicotti.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange filled manicotti in single layer over sauce.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 7.

title: 5 layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar. Pour over
vegetables and chill overnight.
Next day, add bacon bits and tomato just before serving.
Sprinkle cheese over top.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed to boil. Pour over layered vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Serves 15.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse, drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef with seasoning, celery, bell pepper and onion; drain well.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and the cooked macaroni; mix well and warm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, cream cheese and half Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.
Refrigerate left over pie.

title: coke cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Bring to boil the cocoa and Coke and add to creamed mixture.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, which has been greased and floured. Top with marshmallows and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° (usually takes hour).

title: shrimp with linguine or rice(low-fat)
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute in 1/4 cup water or less: onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve over linguine or rice.

title: cheese soup a la tejas
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrot, onion, parsley, seasonings and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Gradually add milk to flour, making sure lumps are blended out.
Gradually add flour mixture to hot vegetables, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add Velveeta and stir until melted.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to boil.
When boiling, turn off heat.
Stir in peanut butter and butter.
Pour over corn flakes. Mix well.
Press on cookie sheet and cool slightly and cut.

title: hasselback potatoes
directions: Flatten potatoes on one side.
Cut 1/4 slices 3/4 way through potato.
Place mixture on top of potatoes and bake in 400° oven 1 hour.
Turn down to 375°.

title: japanese salad
directions: Roast almonds and sesame seed in frying pan until very brown; watch closely, as they
brown easily.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter, mix sugar and pretzels. Pour butter over pretzel mixture. Bake at 350° for 4 minutes. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, and powdered sugar. Spread over pretzels, top with cherry pie filling. Cool before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple chunks.
Spread in container.
(Can be served immediately.)

title: autumn fruit pears and grapes
directions: Soften one package of lemon jello in 1/2 cup water.
Heat 1 1/2 cups water to boiling; add jello along with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until it molds over spoon. Fold in grapes and pears.
Turn into mold.
Chill until firm. Soften other package of jello with 1/2 cup nectar.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling nectar; stir until dissolved.
Stir in salt and remaining lemon juice.
Chill until thickened.
Beat mixture with rotary beater until fluffy.
Add softened cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Turn into mold on top of fruit mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli surprise
directions: Make sauce by cooking over medium heat the butter, flour, milk and bouillon cubes.
Stir and pour over broccoli.

title: don christenson's never-fail pie pastry
directions: Put flour, salt, baking powder and lard in a large bowl. Blend well with a pastry blender.
Combine egg, vinegar and enough cold water to make a cup.
Stir into flour mixture.
Gather up dough with hands; wrap and chill for easier handling.
If well wrapped to prevent drying, this dough may be kept for several days.
It also freezes well.
Defrost it gradually, if frozen.

title: super sausage supper
directions: Saute onion, garlic and carrot in shortening in a skillet. Add sauerkraut, apple cider, wine, pepper, parsley and bay leaf. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Remove bay leaf.
Put into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to box.
Cool for 1/2 hour.
Poke holes in top of cake with a straw.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the cake.
Cool the rest of the way.
Pour ice cream topping over the cake, then spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle crunched Heath bars over top.
Refrigerate.
Best if it is made one day ahead of time.

title: venison roast
directions: Place ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 8 hours. Juice may be thickened for gravy.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Set aside.
Defrost potatoes.
Combine in large bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Add salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend well and pour into greased casserole dish. Cover with butter and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 18 minute cake
directions: Mix together 18 minutes.
Pour into cake pan greased with Crisco and coated with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: johnnie's caramel pecan pie
directions: Combine sugars and flour, mixing well.
Add oleo, eggs, milk and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Pecans will rise to top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: polish potato soup
directions: In a large pot, melt margarine; add kielbasa, onion and celery.
Cook until onion and celery are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except potatoes.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes; cover and cook 20 minutes longer.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt margarine and then add flour and pecans.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add biscuit mix and brown sugar, blending well.
Add nuts; pour batter into well greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This may also be prepared in a larger pan and served as a bar cookie.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, egg and banana.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt that have been mixed together.
Add water; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: nutty banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, beat the bananas and sugar together. Add eggs and shortening. Beat well. Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in nuts.
(Batter will be thick.)
Pour into greased 5 x 9 x 3-inch pan. Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes
out clean. Remove from pan. Cool on rack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and stuffing.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing.
Mix well, then line baking dish with 1/2 stuffing.
Pour ingredients over this.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vegetable spray.
Marinate chicken in salad dressing 3 hours or overnight.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic powder and pepper.
Dredge chicken in bread crumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes or until tender at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first three ingredients for 2 minutes; add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Put in a buttered pan.
Cut after cooling.

title: spinach dip in bread round
directions: Cook spinach and drain between paper towels.
Combine with other ingredients.
Let set overnight for best taste.
Hollow out center of bread and fill with dip.
Break up bread pieces and use for dipping.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to
use. Yields about 1 1/4 cups or about the same amount as 1 (14 ounce) can of commercial type.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Make cake mix according to box; pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach pleasure
directions: Prepare and bake in a rectangular pan 1/2 box of yellow cake mix, following box directions.
Allow cake to cool, then prick throughout with a fork.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water (do not add the usual second cup).
Pour liquid jello over cake. Strain peaches and place them on top of cake.
Prepare instant pudding according to box directions.
Mix prepared pudding and Cool Whip together and spread this topping over the cake and peaches.
Chill and enjoy!

title: easter bunny cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed. Bake in two 8-inch rounds. When cool, cut one layer for ears and bow tie. Assemble bunny head. Frost; sprinkle with coconut. Color a small amount of coconut with red food coloring to make pink; sprinkle pink coconut for inside of bunny ears. Use candy to make bunny face and whiskers and polka dot bow tie.

title: sopa de queso(cheese soup)
directions: Dice onions, carrot and potatoes.
Chop garlic and saute in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Add fresh or canned tomatoes, chopped and seeded, and Ortega chilies.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Add grated Monterey Jack cheese and Colby cheese, mixed together.
Add milk.
Bring to hot temperature, but do not allow to boil.
Your soup is ready to serve.
Enough for 4 cups.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Scramble fry sausage until done.
Pour off grease.
Break cheese into sausage and stir until melted.
Spread on muffin halves.
They freeze well and are good to have for unexpected company.

title: herb butter
directions: Mix all the ingredients together thoroughly in small bowl. Cover and chill to give flavors time to blend.
Let butter soften before serving.
Makes 1/4 cup.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes 24 servings for 2 tablespoons each.

title: brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over meat and marinate for 6 hours. Cover and bake in sauce at 275° for 4 hours.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice, heat in sauce and serve.
(Always slice brisket on the diagonal.)

title: portuguese biscuits
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, then milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add slowly to creamed butter mixture.
Mix well; put on board and knead well. Break in pieces and roll in a ring.
Bake on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar-free orange delight
directions: Gently fold cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and dry gelatin into prepared whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Spoon into individual serving dishes and garnish each serving with strawberry slices and mint, if desired. Yield:
8 servings.
Each Serving:
3/4 cup.
Calories:
78. Exchanges:
1 milk.
Protein:
7 gm.
Fat:
0 mg.
Carbo:
10 gm. Fiber:
Trace.
Sodium:

title: apricot bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour hot water over apricots to cover. Let stand 5 minutes or until softened; drain.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut crusts from bread.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with apricots on each layer.
Beat eggs just enough to blend thoroughly.

title: cauliflower grates with chiles
directions: Cover and
cook
cauliflower
in
small amount of water until tender.
Combine
next 7 ingredients.
Add cauliflower. Spoon into a
buttered 2 quart dish.
Combine butter and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over
casserole.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots and nuts with electric beater.
Fold in carrots and nuts by hand.
Grease 5 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Two 1 pound loaf pans may be used; bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before turning out onto wire rack.

title: linguine with shrimp
directions: Saute garlic in oil until lightly golden.
Put in shrimp. When shrimp are tender, add 1 cup wine or 1/2 cup chicken stock with 1/2 cup wine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook down and let thicken a bit.
Cook linguine al dente.
Pour sauce over linguine. Add cheese.

title: creamy pumpkin tapioca
directions: Spray 1-quart baking dish with Pam.
Mix all ingredients.
Let set 10 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: old fashioned cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt. Mix until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Remove inverted plastic lid over pie crust. Place crust (leave in pie tin) on baking sheet; pour in filling. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg yolks. Add sugar, margarine, and shortening; mix well. Add flour, buttermilk, soda, coconut, pecans, and vanilla. Beat egg whites; fold in. Pour into 3 round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: russian rocks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the flour over fruit and nuts.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining flour, cinnamon, salt and dissolved baking soda.
Lastly, fold in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruited rice and pork chops bake
directions: Brown chops in oil in large skillet; remove from heat.
Add enough water to broth to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add honey, garlic salt and ginger, mixing well.
Pour liquid into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add rice and fruit; stir.
Arrange chops over top.
Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking until all liquid is absorbed, 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, oil and eggs and mix well. Add Rice Krispies, oatmeal and coconut. Grind raisins and add with vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and fold into sugar and cereal mixture. Mix very well. Place in refrigerator and chill for an hour or so. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: layer nacho dip
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate or similar serving dish spread the bean dip to cover bottom.
Combine sour cream with taco seasoning and spread on top of bean dip allowing bottom layer to show around edges.
Do the same with avocado dip, onions, grated cheese, tomatoes, lettuce and ripe olives.
Serve with tortilla chips. Serves 8.

title: phyllis's chicken salad
