directions: Chop celery in food processor; remove.
Chop pecans in food processor; remove.
Chop the chicken in food processor.
Mix all remaining ingredients together with chicken, pecans and celery.

title: apple pecan pie
directions: Cook butter and sugars.
Mix in pecans.
Cook apple.
Mix in sugar, lemon flavoring, cinnamon, cornstarch and water.
Line pie pan with waxed paper.
Pour pecan mixture in.
Make a crust.
Put on top of pecans.
Put apple mixture on top of crust.
Make another crust.
Put on top of apples.
Sprinkle top of crust with cinnamon/sugar.
Put slits in pie crust.
Bake about 25 minutes until golden brown.
Let pie cool 15 minutes, then turn out onto platter.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: aunt nanette's cheese balls
directions: Mix well in food processor or blender.
Form into 2 cheese balls.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in
boiling
water.
Add
cold water, orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Very good. Can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: "blue ribbon" sugar cookies
directions: Beat these ingredients well with mixer.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture well.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
Take out enough to roll out easily.
Pur flour on dough and roll out.
Cut with cookie cutters. Sprinkle with sugar if not going to frost. Bake at 350° about 6 minutes. Be careful to check for browning as each oven is different.

title: turkey 'n' spaghetti summer salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Meanwhile, cook zucchini in small amount of water just until tender.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Place spaghetti, zucchini, turkey, green beans, onions, olives, tomatoes, salt and cheese in a large bowl.
Beat together vinegar, oil, water and salad dressing mix in a small bowl.
Pour over spaghetti mixture and toss lightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.

title: weight watchers salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple with vanilla instant pudding.
Pour over mixed fruit and pineapple.
Let chill.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine first five ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 8-10 minutes. Discard bay leaf. Add remaining ingredients and cover. Simmer 8-10 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: grilled mahimahi on skewers
directions: You will need 24 (10-inch) bamboo skewers.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Trim and peel stems of broccoli and cut a small cross in stem bottom.
Steam until dark green and tender, but not limp.
Trim and chop flower tops of broccoli.
Puree other half of broccoli. Melt butter and gently cook onions and celery until limp.
Stir in flour and poultry broth.
Slowly stir in cream or milk that is at room temperature.
Add salt and black pepper.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Add water and yeast together.
Add buttermilk, sugar and oil. Mix in the dry ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Spoon out enough for 1 meal.
Roll in flour.
Cut out biscuits.
Put in greased pan and bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: lemon strawberry punch
directions: Follow directions on the juice cans and mix with the 7-Up. Blend the strawberries and mix in with the juices.
Then add the ice cream; stir and let a little float.

title: english toffee(yields 1 pound)
directions: *Hershey's mini-morsels are best.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Mix and cook next 3 ingredients.
Cook the spaghetti and salt until done.
Mix all together.

title: vickie's fabulous potato salad
directions: Chop potatoes and onions.
Boil until tender.
Drain and allow to cool completely, about two hours.
In a separate bowl mix all other ingredients together and pour over cool potatoes.
Be sure to salt potatoes while boiling.
Serve immediately or store in refrigerator until later.

title: easy range top treats
directions: In a large saucepan, mix and bring to a boil the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine, stirring occasionally for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and grill meat.
Baste meat with sauce.
Makes meat real tender.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix oil, eggs, sugar and apples well.
Add the dry ingredients and 1 cup chopped nuts (raisins can be added, if desired).
Use a Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Pour 2 cups of hot water over dates and raisins; let stand. Cream sugar, eggs and oleo.
Add dry ingredients.
Add date mix and nuts.
Bake in soup cans.
Grease and flour soup cans.
Fill cans 1/2 full only.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: bean cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by large tablespoon into 1/4 inch hot fat.
Cook, turning once, until brown.
(Can be replacement for meat.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour apple mixture on top of crust. Save a few crumbs to sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time. Add crushed cookies, blending.
Stir in milk.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: pineapple and cheese salad #1
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg and all the juice from the can of pineapple.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring often, and let cool.

title: salsa
directions: Put in food processor just enough to leave chunky.
Simmer until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot or cold.
Great with fajitas or enchiladas.

title: roast and vegetables
directions: In large skillet, brown roast in oil.
Place in a roasting or baking pan.
Add flour to drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir until browned.
Add buttermilk, water, bouillon, thyme and pepper. Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Place carrots and onions around meat; spoon sauce over meat.
Cover; bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in a preheated oven at 350° or until meat is tender.
Add remaining vegetables.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until tender.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well.
Put into casserole dish, then add topping.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: hushwi(stuffing)
directions: Melt butter and add snobar.
Add meat and toss until color turns.
Add to rice.
Add garlic, tomato paste and seasonings.

title: parmesan cheese sticks
directions: Trim crust from bread; cut each slice of bread into 4 strips. Combine crumbs, cheese and garlic salt.
Dip bread sticks in butter; roll in crumb mixture.
Bak at 425° for 7 minutes.

title: tomato spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cake pan. Measure dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add soup and shortening.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and water and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy meatless chili
directions: Dump in crock-pot and enjoy.
This recipe is great for people who need a low sugar and low cholesterol diet.
(You can get the meatless taco filling from me.)

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce and soda, then dry ingredients, raisins and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350°.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Melt butter or margarine over low heat; mix in flour and salt. Heat and stir until bubbly. Add broth slowly, stirring constantly. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and beat 3 minutes. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and pepper in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and refrigerate.

title: asparagus and green pea casserole
directions: Combine mushroom soup with peas in casserole dish.
Layer asparagus on top of peas and soup.
Cover with cheese slices. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easiest ever fudge
directions: Microwave sugar, cocoa, milk and butter on High until butter is melted, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool. Cut in squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken on both sides; cut in bite-size pieces. Cook rice as directed on package. Cook soup (do not add water).

Spread rice in casserole dish; sprinkle chicken over rice, then spread soup over chicken. Sprinkle cheese on top and place in 375° oven long enough to melt cheese. Remove and sprinkle with onion and tomato on top, then serve.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil sugar, water and cherry jello.
Then add almond flavor and pineapple juice.
Place in large container and freeze.
Serve slightly thawed.
Great for parties!

title: pastor's hot spiced chili
directions: Combine ground beef, onions and garlic in large Dutch oven. Cook until beef is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain off pan drippings.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaves.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: mom's banana surprise
directions: Peel bananas and place in a single layer in baking dish, just large enough to hold them.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine pineapple with juice, honey, lemon juice and cornstarch in a bowl; mix together.
Pour over bananas.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sauce will bubble.
Cheap and kids will love it.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cook oats in boiling water; let set until cool.
Cream shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat, then add oat mixture with flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and chopped nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° or until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with a release agent, bringing up around edges slightly. Slice sausage links and distribute evenly over top of crust. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and beat by hand for a few minutes.
Pour over the cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: twenty-four hour cole slaw
directions: Place one-half cabbage in large bowl; cover with onions. Add remaining cabbage. Do not mix. Sprinkle sugar over cabbage.

title: famous black-eyed peas
directions: *Found in Oriental food section.

title: pudding head gingerbread men
directions: Using electric mixer, cream margarine, brown sugar, pudding mix and egg.
Sift flour, baking soda and spices.
Combine flour mixture with creamed mixture; chill.
Roll part of chilled dough out on a floured surface to 1/8 inch thickness.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet to rack to cool.
Decorate.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: lemon parsley clam sauce for linguine
directions: Drain juice from clams and save.
Saute onion and garlic in butter and oil until tender.
Add clam juice and seasonings and simmer 5 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water and let set 3 to 4 minutes.
Put all liquids in a big mixing bowl.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Stir until all is mixed.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
No need to let rise.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator for several days. Bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine 3 cups water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon sticks in a medium saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Strain and pour over tea; let steep 3 minutes.
Strain.
Stir in juices and ice water.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: kay's frozen fruit salad
directions: Layer of lettuce, green onions and Parmesan cheese.
Seal with Hellmann's mayonnaise and let sit overnight.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: chocolate angel food dessert
directions: Melt the chips in a double boiler.
Beat the egg yolks until thick and add to the melted chips while chocolate is still hot. Stir well.
Add sugar and stir well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and pour into the chocolate mixture very slowly.
Whip the cream and add vanilla and salt.
Add this very slowly and carefully to the chocolate mixture.
Tear the cake into small pieces and put a single layer of cake into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half the chocolate over this.
Make another layer of cake; pour the remainder of the chocolate over this.
Chill for 4 hours and serve with whipped cream, topped with a cherry.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Scrub small tender squash and split lengthwise.
Arrange in baking dish and season each with salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Cover generously with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
All will be edible including the skin.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Season pork chops and brown on both sides. Arrange sliced potatoes in 2-quart baking dish. Mix soup, milk and onions and pour over potatoes. Place pork chops over all. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per instructions.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken provencal
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and remove skin.
Mix flour, paprika, basil, salt, oregano, pepper and marjoram.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil in 4-quart Dutch oven until hot.
Cook chicken until brown on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Add olives, carrots, onions and potatoes.
Pour chicken broth over vegetables.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and vegetables and keep warm.
Mix cornstarch and cold water; stir into liquid in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve sauce with chicken.
Makes 8 servings; 298 calories per serving.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat egg and add salt, water, baking powder and flour enough to make a stiff dough. Flour board and roll dough thin. Allow to dry for an hour, then roll dough up like a jelly roll and slice into thin strips. Add noodles to a rich chicken broth.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend for 30 seconds. Makes 3 servings.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Cook macaroni; drain. Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour into buttered dish and bake at 350° until thick (about 30 minutes).
Top with grated cheese and melt in oven.

title: low-fat tuna vegetable pita sandwiches
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Add carrot and next 4 ingredients; toss gently.
Line each pita with 1/2 cup lettuce; fill each with 1/2 cup tuna salad.
Serves 4.
Contains 194 calories; 6.2 grams fat.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Can; process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.
Freeze if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse.

title: putpoluk flat bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water and add to flour with rest of water.
Mix and knead.
Raise to double. Roll about 13 x 17-inches (large cookie sheet).
Raise to double. Prick all over with fork before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Take from oven and brush with oleo.
Cool.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with grated cheese in covered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gorgonzola and green bean salad with pine nuts
directions: Cook green beans; cut in 1/2 or 1/3.
Toast pine nuts.
Mix vinegar, oil, garlic, salt and pepper until well blended.
Toss with beans in the dressing and add the cheese and nuts.
Separate the leaves of radicchio.
Wash and dry.
Arrange on salad plates and spoon the bean salad on top.

title: potato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil potatoes; mash when cooked.
While potatoes are hot, add suet, sugar, salt, raisins and flour (in that order).
Roll out thin on floured surface.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix the day before the salad oil, wine vinegar, honey, pickle relish, pepper and garlic salt.

title: sandy's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Drain mushrooms. Slice mushrooms, olives and red onion.
Add mustard, mayonnaise, olives, mushrooms and onion to potatoes and stir.
Add chopped, boiled eggs and pickle relish.
Refrigerate.

title: sloppy joes for a bunch
directions: Brown hamburger in the microwave and drain. Cook onion until tender in the microwave with olive oil and celery.

Place hamburger in crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients. Stir everything together in the crock-pot and taste. If it seems too sweet, add a little more vinegar. If it seems a little sour, add a little brown sugar. Cook in crock-pot until the olive oil comes to the top. Spoon off as much oil as you can. This should serve a lot of people. It freezes well. If you have a small group and you decide to make half the amount, leave out the Not So Sloppy Joe sauce and put in half of everything else.

title: southern party potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over potatoes into 3-quart (greased) casserole.
Mix 1/4 cup butter and corn flakes; sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches, cornstarch and sugar in a saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil and set aside. In a 9 x 12 baking dish, cut butter into chunks and place on the bottom of dish. Pour mixture into the baking dish. Take biscuits and pinch them into small pieces. Cover top of mixture with biscuit pieces. (Do not dunk under mixture.) Place in oven and bake at 375° until biscuits are brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven
to 325°.	Grease and flour an 8 1/2 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch
loaf
pan.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add	sugar,	eggs,
oil
and
buttermilk.
Stir to blend. Fold in bananas and nuts.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Put in chicken broth, after it comes to a boil, the celery and onion; boil for 5 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add bean sprouts, chicken, mushrooms, soy sauce and Chun King brown sauce. Heat through and serve with rice and noodles.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Put softened cream cheese in bottom of pie plate.
Top with chopped onion, taco sauce, cheese and sliced olives.
Heat in microwave, uncovered, for 14 minutes.
Let cool a little, then serve.
Be careful you don't burn your tongue.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° or until firm.

title: fay's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar well and cook until mixture forms a soft ball in water or candy thermometer. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, chopped nuts, vanilla and marshmallow cream. Beat until smooth. Spread in buttered cookie sheet. Cool; cut in squares.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cool and dice.
Fry bacon; drain.
Brown onions in bacon fat until lightly browned.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in potatoes and crumbled bacon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marzetti
directions: Saute in a frying pan with a little oil the green pepper, celery and onion.
Cook the egg noodles according to package directions.
Cook the hamburger and drain.
Combine soups and salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients together, pouring into the soup mixture, except for the cheese.
Mix together and pour in a greased baking dish.
Add the Cheddar cheese on top of mixture. Cover with foil.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Remove the foil for the last 10 minutes so the top will brown.
Very good!

title: jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water.
Set aside. Follow mixing and baking instructions for the cake mix.
In a chilled deep bowl, mix Dream Whip, pudding and milk, 3 to 8 minutes.
Cool cake 20 to 25 minutes.
Make holes with a fork and pour Jell-O into holes.
Frost with Dream Whip mix.

title: chocolate filled cookies
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Mix sugars, shortening, margarine, vanilla and egg in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Mold 2 level teaspoons of dough around each star.
Place dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 6 to 7 minutes.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and onion.
Add corn and tomato soup. Cook potatoes and mash.
Put all ingredients except potatoes in casserole and spread mashed potatoes on top and spread egg yolk on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Soften butter or oleo in microwave.
Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, dash of nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour in pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding dip(for fruit)
directions: Pour hot pudding into medium size bowl.
Stir in sour cream until blended.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Cover surface of pudding with plastic wrap to prevent skin from forming. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: broccoli and wild rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions.
Combine ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: creme dinucci
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients; then sift in 10x sugar.
Mix and form into a ball.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place in refrigerator.
(If mixture gets too soft to work with, refrigerate for 20 minutes.)
Remove balls from refrigerator and coat in melted chocolate; then roll in crushed peanuts.

title: chess pie
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: 4-bean salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Be sure to drain canned beans.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over mixed beans.
Toss, refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.

title: chicken fritters
directions: In a large bowl, toss together first 4 ingredients.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
In another large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, egg and milk. Blend well.
Add flour mixture to chicken mixture.
In a large frying pan, heat 1-inch of oil to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil and fry in batches, without crowding, for 2 minutes, until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and serve with honey mustard for dipping.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, yeast, sugar, margarine, salt and hot water in a large mixing bowl.
Mix at medium speed for 2 1/2 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of bowl.
Add 1 cup flour; beat on high 1 minute.
Work in remaining flour with a wooden spoon.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May be made ahead of time.
Mix well before serving.
Serve with taco chips or burritos.

title: sloppy joe pocket sandwiches
directions: Combine beef, onion and celery in a large skillet.
Cook until meat is browned. Drain off grease.
Add next 8 ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cut pocket bread in half.
Fill each half with 1/3 cup of the meat mixture.
Yields about 8 sandwiches.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups or 5 servings.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well.
Let set overnight.
You may have to add more dressing.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil the potatoes. Drain and mash. Add rest of ingredients; mix until fluffy.
Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm when knife comes out clean. Add marshmallows on top and brown.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese.
Add Bisquick and sausage.
Make small balls. Freeze on cookie sheet.
Can be put in a bag and kept until ready to bake.
Bake at 375° until brown and crispy, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mandarin icebox pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, then blend in the Cool Whip. Sprinkle a few chopped pecans in the bottom of the crusts.
Pour in milk and fruit mixture and chill.

title: forgotten stew
directions: Rinse and pat dry the meat.
Put in the bottom of a heavy roaster or slow cooker.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer the vegetables in order given.
Mix together the brown sugar, cornstarch and tomato sauce.
Pour over ingredients in cooker.
If using slow cooker, cook on medium to high heat for 5 to 6 hours. If using the oven, place in 275° to 300° oven for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: fried chicken(50 years old)
directions: Always skin chicken.
Get lard or oil hot in iron skillet. Salt and flour chicken.
Put into hot oil and turn on medium heat. Turn often.
Cook until tender and golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken and put on paper towels to drain.
Pour up all but 1/2 cup of the oil and the crunchies.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour in drippings and stir as it browns.
Add 2 to 2 1/2 cups milk slowly, using wire whisk.
Add salt and pepper, if you like it.
Cook until gravy thickens.

title: aunt lottie lane's cake
directions: All ingredients should be room temperature.

title: italian chicken
directions: Pound chicken breast with meat mallet.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Put in dish and pour bottle Italian dressing over the chicken.
Marinate for a few days.
Cook on grill until done.

title: chicken and vegetables(diabetic - low calorie)
directions: Mix chicken, broth, mushrooms, celery, onions and carrot. Stir together water and flour or cornstarch.
Mix vegetables and flour.
Mix together and cook gently until mixture thickens.
Add cubed chicken.
Keep warm.

title: fruit pudding
directions: You may use sugar-free for any of the ingredients.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Lightly grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, soda and spices, then set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat sugar with butter just until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until combined.

title: p. j.
directions: Cut up fruit as desired (apples, pineapple with juice, etc.).

title: sweet 'tater souffle(souffle du chairman)
directions: Cover potatoes with water; simmer until done.
Peel and cut in bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, milk, salt, vanilla and margarine; beat with a mixer until smooth.
Put mixture into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Cover with topping; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruited coleslaw
directions: Toss apples with 1 teaspoon lemon juice in a medium size bowl. Add cabbage, pineapple tidbits and raisins.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl, mixing well.
Pour over cabbage mixture; toss gently.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: crab-cheese appetizer
directions: Mix crab, cream cheese, lemon juice and onion in a quart casserole.
Add cheese to top and bake 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is bubbling.
Serve with toasted wheat crackers.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Prepare pastry to line an 8-inch pie plate. Fill with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Toss cheese with Worcestershire sauce; sprinkle atop pie.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Trim with pickle slices if desired.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix flour and whipping cream together and pour over corn.
Put in oven at 350°; stir 2 to 3 times during baking.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add sour cream, baking soda and vanilla.
Then mix in 2 eggs and 1 cup flour at a time.
Pour into greased tube pan or two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple macadamia nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2
(1-pound)
loaf
pans. Sift the measured flour together with the
baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in the chopped Macadamia nuts.	In
a separate bowl, cream softened butter and the brown sugar.	Stir
in the eggs; beat until mixture is smooth.
In this
order,
stir
in 1/2
of the flour-nut mixture, the pineapple
and
juice
and remaining flour-nut
combination;
blend
thoroughly.
Divide batter	into prepared
pans.
Combine
sugar
and
cinnamon; sprinkle over batter in each pan.
Bake for 50
to 60 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Let cool for 5
minutes, then turn out onto cake rack.
Makes 2 (1-pound) loaves.

title: beatnik cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Blend sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Combine cocoa, oil and vanilla.
Add blended dry ingredients and mix well.
Grind beets before measuring, then add with beaten eggs to batter mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spicy quesadilla rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and jalapenos; spread on soft tortillas. Roll tortillas; cut into bite-size pieces.
Heat in oven until soft.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except strawberries.
Beat 3 minutes; fold in strawberries.
Pour into 3 greased and lightly floured 8-inch layer pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done, 30 or 40 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cut carrots crosswise into 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Drop in saucepan containing a small amount of boiling water and boil about 5 minutes.
Add marmalade.
Cook until tender.
Thicken remaining liquid with cornstarch.

title: cinnamon chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Heat butter, oil and water; bring to a boil and add to dry mixture.
Whisk together eggs, buttermilk, cinnamon and vanilla. Add the whisked mixture in with primary mixture.
Bake in 11 x 18 pan lined with aluminum foil at 375° for 20 minutes or until cake is done.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, sugar and salt together.
Add Milnot.
Pour into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle cake mix evenly and sprinkle nuts and pour oleo over entire dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold with Cool Whip.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in large pan.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Place only 6 to a sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes approximately 90 to 100 cookies.

title: ham and red eye gravy
directions: Place 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet; add ham.
Cook ham until browned.
Repeat with remaining oil and ham.
Remover ham from skillet, reserving drippings in pan.
Add coffee to drippings in pan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Serve gravy and ham with hot biscuits.

title: hot pepper rings
directions: Wash peppers and slice in rings.
Shake out most seeds.
Pack into clean hot jars.
Place 1/2 teaspoon salt in each jar.
Heat enough vinegar to fill jars 1/2-inch from top.
Wipe edges of jars and seal.
Let set.

title: paradise spice cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves in a medium bowl; set aside. Cream the butter and shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add lemon and vanilla extracts, beating well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clear.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove and cool completely. Spread frosting between layers, on sides and top of cake.
Press coconut around sides and sprinkle over top.
Place rhubarb strips in parallel rows on top. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 12 minutes at 325°.

title: mayo cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add last 3 ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening as for pie dough. Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly and knead lightly.
Set at room temperature to rise.
Roll out on floured board and cut out like biscuits.
Place on greased pan and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: de pepe salad(frog eye salad)
directions: Boil macaroni in 4 cups of water for 12 minutes.
Until water boils away.
Set aside to cool.
Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving juice.
Heat juice and thicken with eggs, flour, sugar and salt.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add cooked macaroni to cooled sauce.
Cover and refrigerate over night.
The next morning add fruit, marshmallows and cool whip.
Keeps well up to one week.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix in bowl the coleslaw, onion and apples.
Add dressing, salt and pepper.
Rinse coleslaw dressing bottle with 1/2-inch vinegar to rinse out bottle.
Pour over slaw.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chili cheese bread
directions: Toss baking mix with cheese.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: creole champagne punch
directions: If using fresh pineapple, slice and dice into 1/2-inch wedges.
Rinse and stem strawberries.
Just before serving, combine sugar, lemon and orange juice and curacao in punch bowl. Stir to dissolve sugar completely.
Stir in champagne, wine and club soda.
Add ice ring if desired, then pineapple and strawberries.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: cincinnati chili(makes 8 servings)
directions: Melt butter in large Dutch oven.
Add beef, onion, garlic and bay leaves.
Cook over high heat, stirring to break up large pieces, until beef loses its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Discard bay leaves. Serve over spaghetti and offer side dishes of beans (either red kidney or chili beans), grated American cheese and chopped green onions, to be added as each person wishes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham.
Spread this mixture evenly on one side of each ham slice.
Roll up (long way) and pin with toothpick.
Cover and chill.
Carefully slice each roll into 1/2 inch pieces.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: tomato parmesan cheese chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add seasonings to taste.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle lots of Parmesan cheese on top. Cover and bake.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 4 hours. Garnish with strawberries.

title: peach frosty
directions: Place all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
5 cups (about 72 calories per 1/2-cup serving).

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Cut sausage in 1-inch pieces.
Cut potatoes in quarters.
Cut onion in 1/8-inch slices.
Put cut meat and vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over all.
Add oil and toss.
Cover with foil and bake at 425° for 45 minutes. Uncover and stir in sour cream and peas.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Boil chicken breast.
When done, take out.
Pull chicken off bone.
Put crescent rolls in and roll up as you would regular crescent rolls.
Place in a Pyrex or Corning dish.
Heat broth, soup and cheese together and mix well.
Pour over crescent rolls and place in oven.
Use instructions on roll can to cook by.
When browned on top, take out and serve.

title: banana nut cake(bread)
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition until fluffy.
Add nuts and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour mixture and alternate with bananas and milk a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth. Turn into a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 55 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in parsley and spices.
Blend together eggs and cheese and stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate crescent triangles and place in an ungreased 11-inch quiche pan.
Press over bottom and up sides. Pour in egg-vegetable mixture.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix dip ingredients and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Hollow out the bread to contain the dip.
Cut bread into bite-sized pieces and place on plate around bread.
Just before serving, pour dip into bread cavity.
Dunk and enjoy.

title: easy casserole for a busy day
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: choco-dainties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and salt onto wax paper. Beat together margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla in large bowl until well mixed.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Shape dough into logs, 2 x 1/2-inch.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies are set. Cool on wire racks.
Dip ends of cookies into chocolate coating. Lightly sprinkle on the sprinkles.

title: cheesy chicken, broccoli and rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Bake chicken for 20 to 25 minutes. While chicken is baking, heat soup, milk, water and rice until blended. Place chicken in pan so they lay flat and then pour soup mixture over chicken. Spread a thin layer of cheese on top and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese set out until soft.
Beat with fork or mixer until smooth.
Slowly add drained crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onions and salt.
Mix well.
Pour half of remaining pecans on piece of wax paper.
Roll and press half the mixture in shape of a ball.
Repeat with other half of pecans and mixture. Makes 2 balls.
May freeze.

title: della davis' orange fruit cake
directions: Combine sugar and shortening.
Beat until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well.
Add soda to buttermilk and add to mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add orange peel. Add coconut, nuts and dates.
Bake in tube pan that has been well-greased and floured or sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Mix water, rice, onion and soups together.
Pour in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Layer chicken breasts on top of mixture. Drizzle the melted margarine on top.
Sprinkle on a little paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jack's health drink
directions: A colorful delicious drink that is good for you!

title: good beanie weenies
directions: Preheat oven 375 degrees.
Brown cut-up hot dogs in a small amount of the bacon grease.
In a large bowl add the hot dogs, beans, bacon crumbs, bacon grease, onion, mustard, ketchup, and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Cook 20 minutes (no longer).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar; add milk.
Mix and pour in deep baking dish in which the butter has been melted.
Pile the fruit on top and bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Soak potatoes in water for 10 minutes. Drain and squeeze dry in kitchen towel.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour oil in large skillet to depth of 1/8-inch. Place on medium heat.
For each pancake, pour 1/2 cup mixture into pan.
Flatten lightly. Cook 8 minutes until crispy and brown, turning once. Serve with sour cream and applesauce, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.
